  ('central-park-zoo', 'Central Park Zoo', 'other', 'The Central Park Zoo is a 6.5-acre (2.6 ha) zoo located at the southeast corner of Central Park in New York City. It is part of an integrated system of four zoos and one aquarium managed by the Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS). In conjunction with the Central Park Zoo''s operations, the WCS offers children''s educational programs, is engaged in restoration of endangered species populations, and reaches out to the local community through volunteer programs.', 'The Central Park Zoo is a 6.5-acre (2.6 ha) zoo located at the southeast corner of Central Park in New York City. It is part of an integrated system of four zoos and one aquarium managed by the Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS). In conjunction with the Central Park Zoo''s operations, the WCS offers children''s educational programs, is engaged in restoration of endangered species populations, and reaches out to the local community through volunteer programs.
Its precursor, a menagerie, was founded in 1864, becoming the first public zoo to open in New York. The present facility first opened as a city zoo on December 2, 1934, and was part of a larger revitalization program of city parks, playgrounds and zoos initiated in 1934 by New York City Department of Parks and Recreation (NYC Parks) commissioner Robert Moses. It was built, in large part, through Civil Works Administration and Works Progress Administration (WPA) labor and funding. The Children''s Zoo opened to the north of the main zoo in 1960, using funding from a donation by Senator Herbert Lehman and his wife Edith.
After 49 years of operation as a city zoo run by NYC Parks, Central Park Zoo closed in 1983 for reconstruction. The closure was part of a five-year, $35 million renovation program, that completely replaced the zoo''s cages with naturalistic environments. It was rededicated on August 8, 1988, as part of a system of five facilities managed by the WCS, all of which are accredited by the Association of Zoos and Aquariums (AZA).', 'Manhattan', 'Central Park', 'New York, NY 10021', 40.7677061, -73.9719906, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMm8NCz3fkbnOEcrsYiFeSPqGXHrR_Xb4syWfK9DYFriHMQp6CiopCqEchCMLDsyMftRWKyd_DGRFW8gASRU3mQewKHgE0tG6iKIbT7KXB0HHpi6C5YrpF2v5XlxY_-P_ECBN5tIWcZQC8B=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZN8T7xDQr9lioj9YA3H1mE6P4Is-pAzkvmOnzMdMo6a4L4w-FCzL1KEOhRna8dvJ5Ooa4YBDZ75etr4-Uq_1sHRIiptivM4ndLNWtpIoufof1Q2ZLAjyJpVZ0ekJ9rbgsDXd3JLX9meAEQed2st6g1V=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZP9TcqUehNlWcTOe6C_g-xtbkMgRSfQFKFgJVEc_yyXunQDR6nW8qVybqCooPCzCha1fIAvOmcPY1J3cIUY2jAYmH_-kXHSa2bFdzNxNkVB8RDFmiMJNTVYCL6dwl0TL9MDz7R3yvQSmXQ=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZP_KSqoG5JrT7lg6nun4OECNTzOBjDYVdrl3L3xjhRdNPUaMB3_U9yzvH4VD2EFvf14KNUi5iFDixVa4Jrq7KREIkAIGbDXPsnnFcOKeg-xJ5Hy1mOfjUSgx1IwVDc-7wOMylTiAMQsbomyUg=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "tue": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "sat": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "sun": [["10:00", "17:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 10:00–17:00', 'ChIJaWjW_PFYwokRFD8a2YQu12U', 4.4, 26115.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 120, '5 Av/59 St (N,R,W)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJaWjW_PFYwokRFD8a2YQu12U', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Central+Park+Zoo&query_place_id=ChIJaWjW_PFYwokRFD8a2YQu12U', 'https://centralparkzoo.com/', '+1 212-439-6500', ARRAY['zoo', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('bethesda-terrace', 'Bethesda Terrace', 'landmark', 'Bethesda Terrace and Fountain are two architectural features overlooking the southern shore of the Lake in New York City''s Central Park. The fountain, with its Angel of the Waters statue, is located in the center of the terrace.', 'Bethesda Terrace and Fountain are two architectural features overlooking the southern shore of the Lake in New York City''s Central Park. The fountain, with its Angel of the Waters statue, is located in the center of the terrace.
Bethesda Terrace''s two levels are united by two grand staircases and a lesser one that passes under Terrace Drive. They provide passage southward to the Central Park Mall and Naumburg Bandshell at the center of the park. The upper terrace flanks the 72nd Street Cross Drive and the lower terrace provides a podium for viewing the Lake. The mustard-olive colored carved stone is New Brunswick sandstone, with a harder stone for cappings, with granite steps and landings, and herringbone pattern paving of Roman brick laid on edge.', 'Manhattan', 'Central Park', 'New York, NY 10024', 40.7739528, -73.97096570000001, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZN67mUBscF6gl-HIZthceXCPBI0VFSIXayA7vxFeVM1JOxgl-C6zQ9zaDY9MBW5JWwHwZbPZUXsX0rsKxboFUQ5OTFeZZD_kAYHF0fql2JPa852bQsZn4YjhB59CYiRZg6GvfNp3jWGgVrx=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPzaHC_Jn18xbMduDg3tmKkeGW-7kW_7_vwH6tQkl9hB39eWN0cTsRdv6GlNEYVqbLVLLzaYul2ombnfgIaCOxNpAioRiKRWzTWxUGAk1ThnPTrB-p9pioHJMdpVCY_NelGvcrGH_QADqM=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOcgPEsXaRwBYVIOW5HlMEjVr2q2PzKGyV5Sp8I6LollboD3fco2Fhs7tD7psLQ8BYk8ci5ej3RjS41fasIZl2A1lozU3nhZrTdUdeOGx3aLo-OS0R4ougi0NaWimZky8jMC8U0oXkSN6bsD111-rm9=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPkVZ41TKOc4PyBzAFWngpUOlFfgNPPrC50zQRdB5N2X6XG1CCPsL6awuHQlZQBiiCgypdH8jYE2qQyYO03952QBI9v_m8apKfFlQNJS8mnZto3wkECa0eT_MRi1S5Xlllz6vOstshuKseh=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "01:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–01:00', 'ChIJEYYWppJYwokRUTul6ztwlJ0', 4.7, 12054.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, '72 St (C,B)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJEYYWppJYwokRUTul6ztwlJ0', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Bethesda+Terrace&query_place_id=ChIJEYYWppJYwokRUTul6ztwlJ0', 'https://www.centralparknyc.org/locations/bethesda-terrace', '(212) 310-6600', ARRAY['historical_landmark', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('strawberry-fields', 'Strawberry Fields', 'landmark', 'Strawberry Fields is a 2.5-acre landscaped section in New York City''s Central Park, designed by the landscape architect Bruce Kelly, that is dedicated to the memory of former Beatles member John Lennon. It is named after the Beatles'' song "Strawberry Fields Forever", written by Lennon. The song itself is named for the former Strawberry Field children''s home in Liverpool, England, located near Lennon''s childhood home.', 'Strawberry Fields is a 2.5-acre (1.0 ha) landscaped section in New York City''s Central Park, designed by the landscape architect Bruce Kelly, that is dedicated to the memory of former Beatles member John Lennon. It is named after the Beatles'' song "Strawberry Fields Forever", written by Lennon. The song itself is named for the former Strawberry Field children''s home in Liverpool, England, located near Lennon''s childhood home.', 'Manhattan', 'Central Park', 'Q2GG+83, New York, NY 10019', 40.7757544, -73.97520759999999, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNNV554UzSOieiacD9TrXySSd-onXeUo9yxyC5h0IsKRpV320RTZk_Ae3akjuboGAcSffAIDrUEt6cLFme79zMmXaAAY67cMXtNkQoZmpFJvkjYAWG1G6Bzr9sYMEExDNPpTqVneQ9bEFE=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZP1dMMDIDZcqGzaTlr5nEGCWoRN3ZHiMonY2LEG7NTZ99PpxY0UCdqG6O3dLmSIArGy7edC10nFkuZZFwnhZ8-Cp8hkT2SZQqBW5MiMDBlsabuHnD0VD6qb4NXxxqw4E_LYDVZ0zQuLQtErAaHTVjY=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPow-Y-K6PekVsYSb7vldzHMt_WwRutOzvd9YKUc3OfkJPoVi_Wqqho1uWPo2umAEZmJT4V1P7ErTGu1GEG6HXiOcWNZPzO9-MjiaMcB6OFOjMWprKdX7vAvgp5tGVlWq6DWMAuOxpyK9xB=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPtDp6ITO81fWvJ3DG_2_fsSJu75iy4LE0NZtf5b3LrFe2l7VjmcV0jSIsqdqVrzT37bqjvf9OjuR8O9Vy0UfelCnuhvayKgo0NSyTl0GEke7gXyMo_MEukr50nT1VgbtHOaip7B6s4ZSzg=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "fri": 