  ('belvedere-castle', 'Belvedere Castle', 'landmark', 'Belvedere Castle is a folly in Central Park in Manhattan, New York City. It contains exhibit rooms, an observation deck, and since 1919 has housed Central Park’s official weather station.', 'Belvedere Castle is a folly in Central Park in Manhattan, New York City. It contains exhibit rooms, an observation deck, and since 1919 has housed Central Park’s official weather station.
Belvedere Castle was designed by Calvert Vaux and Jacob Wrey Mould in 1867. An architectural hybrid of Romanesque and Gothic styles, the design called for a Manhattan schist and granite structure with a corner tower and conical cap, a lookout over parapet walls beneath it. Its name comes from belvedere, which means "beautiful view" in Italian.', 'Manhattan', 'Central Park', 'New York, NY 10024', 40.7794302, -73.9690677, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNPzwBGVx78lvBLmJw26KzWzrXVn6tUzb0NaXmurJ6XROQLTs92o6tsCn08sDIsoyf2Um2Kwug02gewTMfZqKmwZ1GOHnDqP8aLfR2Bih4vUEyYFlQOoHIn2kjlFsYgvXKSxQts4B-6SLoA=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPRvAx8mhB1JMWy7KGQL3xnupaz-kZR3Y_VGO4pYGI0JKegB8HPIKJ-8l9qIO6wZ93OGKEMtoC-pgj8NFLSYYjxg4pY2W7YNkD80LqjJe72qYAflURpRUt1hv7BjGnaOdwb2yoSGDh1SN3oSLTstww=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMytSC6qvi8i_4jLVuWAIIcS2KQzkzUbpr02ohTMzP2lIwWIJor8q6bNYZBwz34fKQV_Ekk2TYjISFRyOY3P9UGadvOsJ88LB-bK3LOaeHB33ZBUTNaoIGCJk1-Y2S2XHoE3R4JJhoHFSi8=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPBfGkyrnLyx67hwDHXOjrTcqp_OUxztfUCOAsKITPbd2Hz5w8u52b65ox2SN78LPtHvCUNGrltzLuopT9j8ZNN6SpMqy1g2GMa8xxz-KVsqLjaual2vvw9T9dK4932_NUSUXnmV8cm98EpQB1UH0df=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "tue": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "sat": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "sun": [["10:00", "17:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 10:00–17:00', 'ChIJFXzf4e9YwokRtXgpty_i74g', 4.5, 7124.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, '81 St-Museum of Natural History (C,B)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJFXzf4e9YwokRtXgpty_i74g', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Belvedere+Castle&query_place_id=ChIJFXzf4e9YwokRtXgpty_i74g', 'https://www.centralparknyc.org/locations/belvedere-castle', '(332) 213-3947', ARRAY['castle', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('wollman-rink', 'Wollman Rink', 'other', 'Wollman Rink is a public ice rink in the southern part of Central Park, Manhattan, New York City. It is named after the Wollman family who donated the funds for its original construction. The rink is open for ice skating from late October to early April. From 2003 until 2019, Victorian Gardens, a seasonal amusement park for children, was operated on the site from late May to September.', 'Wollman Rink is a public ice rink in the southern part of Central Park, Manhattan, New York City.  It is named after the Wollman family who donated the funds for its original construction. The rink is open for ice skating from late October to early April. From 2003 until 2019, Victorian Gardens, a seasonal amusement park for children, was operated on the site from late May to September.
Wollman Rink opened in 1950, having been proposed four years earlier.  The rink was closed for renovations in late 1980 and reopened in November 1986. Following the renovation, The Trump Organization operated the rink under contract with the New York City government until 1995 and again from 2001 until 2021, when control was given to Wollman Park Partners, a joint venture formed between Harris Blitzer Sports & Entertainment, The Related Companies, and Equinox Group.', 'Manhattan', 'Central Park', 'Q29G+46, 830 5th Ave, New York, NY 10065', 40.7677792, -73.9744673, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPKn55v1vWVERP9MV69hTMaeyUcuYkIj0IySNZ4SJbWnmqtWTG-6FHDxEq8oqXX9Q9OePKBmpI40wMqKm1KFH7wxnZzJnXKldVO8hrvqhlVhwDqdIHad5vUMROnXDFRhz-e8E7ifweg8w-A=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPWaDmSp5vIQdc4GLclSoRxT_ihBA-Sf7BjUN84PfOwL4tzoFmwy1fdOip1RruEPy7lVl9WO6i19YT0JHMa4zGiUV0oSbFbQpHlRB_KP4RaHnL6lenVBL2WKLOjtP9M9mKcU7JYoq1Duh-D=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM-ByXET7HPlkUrYHIJ9tUmUotWVB9N_SpkQ6AirW12HPxij384iJaZw8QpDQ5RrbWmz-tEpW1AmkXxobQuJQjgoLHJdluBnuDTKiFwkmllb1AG-HB1vaJlRRLg1CoxuKSc0MIPrQYS4fCc=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNLdBP4UzlC5GHyjAuL-_9-LbUlaLwJ24bGuNj4Nu3ffQwwV8qBgFH0-xhQ-EMF4P01yWxcQBWhPkuV1DGjMjo8gEtMz1pzZWigSBZz0MWzGS9gFOVS71-t77EkiP5bKsNSlkQJua7mR0Sa=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["08:00", "21:00"]], "tue": [["08:00", "21:00"]], "wed": [["08:00", "21:00"]], "thu": [["08:00", "21:00"]], "fri": [["08:00", "21:00"]], "sat": [["08:00", "21:00"]], "sun": [["08:00", "21:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 08:00–21:00', 'ChIJeelsevFYwokRqyH7P0aN2C8', 4.3, 1228.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '5 Av/59 St (N,R,W)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJeelsevFYwokRqyH7P0aN2C8', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Wollman+Rink&query_place_id=ChIJeelsevFYwokRqyH7P0aN2C8', 'https://wollmanrinknyc.com/', '+1 833-615-3500', ARRAY['ice_rink', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('intrepid-museum', 'Intrepid Museum', 'museum', 'The Intrepid Museum is a military, aerospace, and history museum in New York City, United States. It is located at Pier 86 at 46th Street, along the Hudson River, in the Hell''s Kitchen neighborhood on the West Side of Manhattan. The museum is composed of exhibits, aircraft, and the Space Shuttle Pavilion aboard the museum ship USS Intrepid, a World War II–era aircraft carrier and National Historic Landmark. Its collections include a cruise missile submarine named USS Growler and a Concorde on Pier 86. The Intrepid Museum Foundation, a 501(c)(3) organization established in 1979, operates the museum.', 'The Intrepid Museum (originally the Intrepid Sea, Air & Space Museum) is a military, aerospace, and history museum in New York City, United States. It is located at Pier 86 at 46th Street, along the Hudson River, in the Hell''s Kitchen neighborhood on the West Side of Manhattan. The museum is composed of exhibits, aircraft, and the Space Shuttle Pavilion aboard the museum ship USS Intrepid, a World War II–era aircraft carrier and National Historic Landmark. Its collections include a cruise missile submarine named USS Growler and a Concorde on Pier 86. The Intrepid Museum Foundation, a 501(c)(3) organization established in 1979, operates the museum.
The museum was proposed in the late 1970s as a way to preserve Intrepid, and it opened on August 3, 1982. The Intrepid Museum Foundation filed for bankruptcy protection in 1985 after struggling to attract visitors. The foundation acquired USS Growler and the destroyer USS Edson in the late 1980s to attract guests and raise money, although it remained unprofitable through the 1990s. The museum received a minor renovation in 1998 after it started turning a profit. Between 2006 and 2008, the Intrepid Museum was completely closed for a $115 million renovation. A new pavilion for the Space Shuttle Enterprise opened in 2012.
The Intrepid Museum spans three of the carrier''s decks; from top to bottom, they are the flight, hangar, and gallery decks. Most of the museum''s collection is composed of aircraft, many of which were used by the United States Armed Forces. Among the museum''s collection are a Concorde SST, a Lockheed A-12 supersonic reconnaissance plane, and the Space Shuttle Enterprise. The hangar and gallery decks contain a variety of attractions such as exhibit halls, a theater, and flight simulators, as well as individual objects like a cockpit and an air turbine. Several craft and other objects have been sold off or removed from the museum''s collection over the years. The museum serves as a space for community and national events, such as Fleet Week and awards ceremonies, in addition to educational programs.', 'Manhattan', 'Hell''s Kitchen', 'Pier 86, W 46th St, New York, NY 10036', 40.764880100000006, -74.0008306, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOK9SJNaamexuqXZxyxzGVEYgfrCspmgq0jeGhrUaYS1IDtGvH8pqzafKpcWrk_T84VNsaJF_AtVryLiqJLAuHiDToFi7dnXERPhNPzsmdNXSjHQJQlFy2Tgt-HL8SHH2qfvL0OiDGTyzaOyQ=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMH0OrU1utRW7_yw8bHI5wiTCXsJtpRyvZl4G_HsHOTbPxZi4bfapmiCgufoIf3gb-fxz0EvmnozpeOP3P7HAxNfLXiDtLD7yzNG6q1Q07SBDg_rGH3DU1lHcSvjNMdv3NnUtxAknKy3BPReQ=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPMdWZcvI1tMfnntDOjBTOlqZBgihq_6MfJ16ApO6kMfBamEEbcvGtRLnOyyDZFsYno95gT7WT4rFiNJ3mM4cnm8WrWR9WC0USFZeY4VqKcUBRivBEVv3MGz-HBUfnarmk95zdGQZZbz1Re=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPbUZezT6IYuqFC7jrSoVAvzXkJyzo6QCQgEY3jtfA62XPZg31Ye5u6QP-GKWTSSqYFT1TysNDcWSWlwKiv57ftkA-EtIs5nwFivaSfgEWvYDttwwdnpYjoxPifCuUQfP2mVcFPemBtOoSG=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "tue": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "sat": [["10:00", "18:00"]], "sun": [["10:00", "18:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Mon–Fri 10:00–17:00; Sat–Sun 10:00–18:00', 'ChIJnxlg1U5YwokR8T90UrZiIwI', 4.7, 46522.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 90, '34 St-Hudson Yards (7)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJnxlg1U5YwokR8T90UrZiIwI', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Intrepid+Museum&query_place_id=ChIJnxlg1U5YwokR8T90UrZiIwI', 'https://www.intrepidmuseum.org/', '(212) 245-0072', ARRAY['museum', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('tenement-museum', 'Tenement Museum', 'museum', 'The Lower East Side Tenement Museum is a museum and National Historic Site located at 97 and 103 Orchard Street on the Lower East Side of Manhattan in New York City, United States. The museum''s two historical tenement buildings were home to an estimated 15,000 people, from over 20 nations, between 1863 and 1935 and 1888 and 2015. The museum, which includes a visitors'' center, promotes tolerance and historical perspective on the immigrant experience.', 'The Lower East Side Tenement Museum is a museum and National Historic Site located at 97 and 103 Orchard Street on the Lower East Side of Manhattan in New York City, United States. The museum''s two historical tenement buildings were home to an estimated 15,000 people, from over 20 nations, between 1863 and 1935 (97 Orchard Street) and 1888 and 2015 (103 Orchard Street). The museum, which includes a visitors'' center, promotes tolerance and historical perspective on the immigrant experience.', 'Manhattan', 'Lower East Side', '103 Orchard St, New York, NY 10002', 40.718818, -73.9900876, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMx2PcaJZJARXMT6jvVJe58MxYKb8MRy51QLQPhKO_r8ZpPsTnTsvhfFeld9IXfqKP05-U1k0cozke63wQHm4obPVaT6WfOh0aj-pxdClWvMIOSTQU5r4VfUHSNiaWFimYX2Lftqg4iAq-z=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPf90gaEYDNCsGMdiTHILvpxduUygJ53dlagN443bfsKcUFv5ketaE4uf7OKsxGnt7OwImbB7KtLMiA1nyNmepP8dMXxvMV_WkumdVVwnFINtP55vpD53BbkIrU4zPWU7dH5FLGET3ErQ7C=s4800-w567', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOtPRJU3JCGC4Uqz33vmAynwd5uLA6CBvDywg4V7oggHym_U6zlyg4OIKpzojG3zdj88vdqEv2lbStII9RIJW2A6ffAaGA8xky511WnLkx0I21YaDkn1AnBqpotdGhSKSH22vINZOQHPPMX8CvIpmg=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNbkMQpoIpQQ2Rk0N5AOWqwUxTGhW9gZOsUmPYEX4Zeh2m8dRH_TB6jShe07ML_Qw2ee6vAVhAjE0MMorpkrf8llLCMn_oP9_nSckQnHfn4GwlKJmEMSQrl7PqM_ECcDIkJQcUcxrrwMHw7=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "18:00"]], "tu