  ('rubin-museum-of-art', 'Rubin Museum of Art', 'gallery', 'The Rubin Museum of Himalayan Art, also known as the Rubin Museum or the Rubin Museum of Art, is dedicated to the collection, display, and preservation of the art and cultures of the Himalayas, the Indian subcontinent, Central Asia and other regions within Eurasia, with a permanent collection focused particularly on Tibetan art. The museum opened in 2004 at 150 West 17th Street between the Avenue of the Americas and Seventh Avenue in the Chelsea neighborhood of Manhattan in New York City. In early 2024 it announced the closure of its New York City building in order to become a global "museum without walls", focusing on traveling exhibitions, long-term loans, partnerships, and digital resources. 
The museum closed on October 6, 2024.', NULL, 'Manhattan', 'Chelsea-Hudson Yards', '140 W 17th St, New York, NY 10011', 40.7399603, -73.9973455, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNe675W5xFtK_JaBVFXSYTazRh3kjj34yaBFeBJrQhHhH2eNYXvnEUW9f3VufmIzNfU5g41c_SE8ZX3e521fOMBe9Jc7aBEj6xW4MY68MZtCnGA3hEm4mQGo6l79GVmQ6HnJbzZaVE0EkLL=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMxTRMA2zwiuluL_knzDeFLh-5P2UNn7Z0i4REjD738siSm_xkuoyA20aAM0SCJanlrGKdgVTCc-VlmjugWelcO3NK3sn7iLYac0csdmYaDe_nDA8ALBKyYvb6Zb8MCBvpiig97eICzAiAQeg=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPiPixznh4g5ASegeMn-UVkIpTJr2fNCO2qPfYXVw4sE_imNGJYfIJyzWwOP4i1jTzV7_QRT_JYkuSR7Okw05cHwsRL2zi1snr9FnrOg20XKp61zugHmtnNZM_noJmaY5dBnBFU1dTfSZsfhQ=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNLnMQaW5cJ0AxRzVDHUtQCXoTY4YkmBTsWgP1v11r0gZL40bslMaeYF2Jj5eIpC6FBqi0YwOKBPSomak58W1I2y3WSJ1wQeOlC6f3ssrxiftWDs8vdFjna_yhLmikqd327B_g069nGs-y3=s4800-w800']::text[], NULL, 'Th-Su 11:00-17:00; Fr 11:00-22:00', 'ChIJD4QSVbxZwokRaFPDajZtIaI', 4.6, 2167.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 60, '18 St (1)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJD4QSVbxZwokRaFPDajZtIaI', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Rubin+Museum+of+Art&query_place_id=ChIJD4QSVbxZwokRaFPDajZtIaI', 'https://rubinmuseum.org/', '+1-212-620-5000', ARRAY['association_or_organization', 'museum', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('museum-of-the-city-of-new-york', 'Museum of the City of New York', 'museum', 'The Museum of the City of New York (MCNY) is a history and art museum in Manhattan, New York City. It was founded by Henry Collins Brown in 1923 to preserve and present the history of New York City and its people. It is located at 1220–1227 Fifth Avenue between East 103rd to 104th Streets, across from Central Park on Manhattan''s Upper East Side, at the northern end of the Museum Mile section of Fifth Avenue.', 'The Museum of the City of New York (MCNY) is a history and art museum in Manhattan, New York City. It was founded by Henry Collins Brown in 1923 to preserve and present the history of New York City and its people. It is located at 1220–1227 Fifth Avenue between East 103rd to 104th Streets, across from Central Park on Manhattan''s Upper East Side, at the northern end of the Museum Mile section of Fifth Avenue.
The red brick with marble trim museum was built in 1929–30 and was designed by Joseph H. Freedlander in the neo-Georgian style, with statues of Alexander Hamilton and DeWitt Clinton by sculptor Adolph Alexander Weinman facing Central Park from niches in the facade.
The museum is a private non-profit organization which receives government support as a member of New York City''s Cultural Institutions Group. Its other sources of income are endowments, admission fees, and contributions.', 'Manhattan', 'East Harlem (South)', '1220 5th Ave, New York, NY 10029', 40.7924939, -73.95190889999999, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNB9v-q8NkHQT3-IClP8kmFudQ6dD80gmPh6qi5mt4OGJEzuxVpKGY8Bk7eSfJOFqGFetBw7ycPoU42AD548YU_KNtAfyLH_k9mNklyHQppRs2CjFMzZ1cSZ45Ux-Pr2IO4S8vzXNz8iDYx=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNc-TmEyqEIOvzxxHhRnVDrMJhY3jjuIyNG05MKt039SDVhBJD0cT0kTaFaI5ayONefpPmWn1WDo5UZy50q70TaetDgT-JG_5ldoxYPmoj-TOjT9q9a48eoxl2w295bqr9D_hT4lyq13620=s4800-w700', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMTno8sISBYN07KQ5ED08Kjx_mFRrkIh_o7t6F82ORA9hfcLnc-BzCOXfdy3h_puSucZ6j94_P4BJ2Ss0GkanVkOQSmgyYGOxu3OIwjpvgUgtq_0RVfzo13zDsHVQruh9GWAWstCxBiF3XZjQ=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMHPiPhMCjCAObtu3OWxi2dYeUi1dFe9eu3HqynENkdALpD-hrx5qNExb-oThgsjCfpeX6XwGH4A8XR_wChGmJ5U6BsBKjxnuWYZcLzDnSqJMiDB2SMY2VYPtQQmTQBaEDyUPOTkg0Jz_FI=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "tue": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["10:00", "17:00"]], "sat": [["10:00", "18:00"]], "sun": [["10:00", "18:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Mon–Fri 10:00–17:00; Sat–Sun 10:00–18:00', 'ChIJi4hYtB32wokR1Npx_Tv7phk', 4.5, 6336.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 90, '103 St (6)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJi4hYtB32wokR1Npx_Tv7phk', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Museum+of+the+City+of+New+York&query_place_id=ChIJi4hYtB32wokR1Npx_Tv7phk', 'https://www.mcny.org/', '(212) 534-1672', ARRAY['museum', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('el-museo-del-barrio', 'El Museo del Barrio', 'museum', 'El Museo del Barrio, often known simply as El Museo, is a museum at 1230 Fifth Avenue in Upper Manhattan, New York City. It is located near the northern end of Fifth Avenue''s Museum Mile, immediately north of the Museum of the City of New York. Founded in 1969, El Museo specializes in Latin American and Caribbean art, with an emphasis on works from Puerto Rico and the Puerto Rican community in New York City. It is the oldest museum of the country dedicated to Latino art.', 'El Museo del Barrio, often known simply as El Museo (the museum), is a museum at 1230 Fifth Avenue in Upper Manhattan, New York City. It is located near the northern end of Fifth Avenue''s Museum Mile, immediately north of the Museum of the City of New York. Founded in 1969, El Museo specializes in Latin American and Caribbean art, with an emphasis on works from Puerto Rico and the Puerto Rican community in New York City. It is the oldest museum of the country dedicated to Latino art.', 'Manhattan', 'East Harlem (South)', '1230 5th Ave, New York, NY 10029', 40.7931183, -73.9514063, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNnFvyonBDbCB9QDVap0d-SialvX41ZShCUsPjaEn1dNgdpKpE6ykuib1vnihShPWDMzrmhGhOFieDwEUOI4w5rzhE3YBnrzynz-cowzySiE9_4_iY-U54MthLzY-pTtLKSV-9QT04UEyrYoQ=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZN-xlQjG50yQNK_RsvrbjP6Ww4J-viRccHJO4OiCX4491iWLebeDbW_vU5en6ss4APeOjOuxNhVv8pas3XIMSLuhmNH0rmKnY4k4qISVgJJfdlQAIskuPfpTg_ItL_NzpQOfGoY655ds6kw=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZO3F5Z-Q3VqeHhoz97A6xHXgXrTatXw_J9Wm_v43UXi3XMwhH_sqgNjnkBDMowN_l9s3j7bleYMhYDgApLADoDoMUlZOBvc_8ktV_Y1OEeomt2l54n6Tlbd5w1YjUSRBZjQxQ_eS5pTrZAJNNZ805rO=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPaIOZQV4x7XSHF756_Xzj5Z1Z_oCy7k58yiT0Nb6RQ27RisGSoQBhKi_GuJQpit7AgPRg55DrAuKMT0Om2xE4y-A1rthqoL7lp_60JkG1kwkEQ4YZiKsEWEHJQzUwSKqV1RcSbRLr1RK6G=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": null, "tue": null, "wed": null, "thu": [["11:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["11:00", "17:00"]], "sat": [["11:00", "17:00"]], "sun": [["11:00", "17:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Thu 11:00–17:00; Fri 11:00–17:00; Sat 11:00–17:00; Sun 11:00–17:00', 'ChIJWT0gUBz2wokRNcAxVUphAAs', 4.4, 955.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 90, '103 St (6)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJWT0gUBz2wokRNcAxVUphAAs', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=El+Museo+del+Barrio&query_place_id=ChIJWT0gUBz2wokRNcAxVUphAAs', 'https://elmuseo.org/', '(212) 831-7272', ARRAY['museum', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('the-jewish-museum', 'The Jewish Museum', 'museum', 'The Jewish Museum is an art museum housed at 1109 Fifth Avenue, in the Felix M. Warburg House, along the Museum Mile on the Upper East Side of Manhattan, New York City. The museum holds a collection of approximately 30,000 objects, including religious artifacts, fine art, and media, making it one of the largest museums dedicated to the Jewish culture worldwide. The museum is known for its expansive cultural and historical scope, staging art exhibitions that center "Jewish heritage and viewpoints while appealing to broader audiences".', 'The Jewish Museum is an art museum housed at 1109 Fifth Avenue, in the Felix M. Warburg House, along the Museum Mile on the Upper East Side of Manhattan, New York City. The museum holds a collection of approximately 30,000 objects, including religious artifacts, fine art, and media, making it one of the largest museums dedicated to the Jewish culture worldwide. The museum is known for its expansive cultural and historical scope, staging art exhibitions that center "Jewish heritage and viewpoints while appealing to broader audiences".
The Jewish Museum originated in 1904 with Judge Mayer Sulzberger''s donation of ceremonial objects to the Jewish Theological Seminary, later expanded through gifts and works sent for safekeeping from Poland in 1939 due to the outbreak of World War II. The museum was established in the Warburg family mansion, donated in 1944 by Frieda Warburg, and opened to the public in 1947. Originally designed by C.P.H. Gilbert in the châteauesque style, the building underwent expansions in 1959 and 1963.
Appointed director in 1972, Joy Ungerleider-Mayerson oversaw the acquisition of 600 ancient artifacts from Israel and the 1975 exhibition Jewish Experience in the Art of the 20th Century. Under Joan Rosenbaum''s directorship (1981–2010), introduced new public initiatives—most notably the launch of the New York Jewish Film Festival in 1992—and completed a major renovation in 1993 by Kevin Roche, who added 11,000 square feet and modernized the facilities for exhibitions and education while preserving the building''s Gothic revival character. In 2006, the museum adjusted its Sabbath observance policy by opening to the public on Saturdays. In 2011, Claudia Gould was appointed Helen Goldsmith Menschel Director and served in this role until her retirement in 2023. She was succeeded by James S. Snyder in November 2023.
Throughout its history, the Jewish Museum has made important contributions to the study of modern and contemporary art in the United States. Described as a "leading arbiter of mid-20th-century American art", it played host to the first solo museum exhibitions of painters Helen Frankenthaler, Kenneth Noland, and Ad Reinhardt; introduced Jasper Johns to the broader public through the 1957 Artists of the New York School: Second Generation; staged the first museum retrospective of Robert Rauschenberg in 1963; and presented the influential 1966 exhibition Primary Structures that helped launch Minimalist sculpture.', 'Manhattan', 'Upper East Side-Carnegie Hill', '1109 5th Ave &, E 92nd St, New York, NY 10128', 40.785334, -73.957351, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMXsNrkOTbzpSdX22VX2YZU-1O3T7awTjHGNZSC6heBoe_aRJZNsXe_bqgi5q0Bc_L37GU2DT2KDhhKNMAFie9HA9IKUdTRA7Dzh-D_XR5WcB0zWQ4cowQRaLPToozoZOzFaXYwxSDofLsmqKoU6Fo=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM01nVkcARBOBkpbWgZU7XIT8KFClNm6gsdz7ouah6WJDfWbWUqWnNk71Hsup0wijszk11WFlD6TDrB2DZxX0brSZ0YNxUQ8jkVK_dny_zX6WJUZNrsmFGrrubyGHkoKFoBoziiWXWwDP-v=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPy_x9BZ10Ef1cmT-yzGKvt3hPC7Wtl511ksjdofVTQ63Chy9SjV9foUGO3hbuSge2nnx9pOmW2uptW1bBG1tedxzKvSXJdGovg3rr4m6a1jwoC65hMDRYBG4gV9_FC_nuyaOhq-oq1NNRYGA=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOix_zwNwq4WfdnQv-jLlacI2nbDyAy_hgOUjNySxS1XZ9c7HFa0x5p4fjY0JTvuVJ2osbHq9Cn1TjY64t3nIYVOPGQqqR0GtO5azt8eh20bGIQXNT2bWumohkHhf-gZbFN39tUDPTxJk2x=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["11:00", "18:00"]], "tue": null, "wed": null, "thu": [["11:00", "20:00"]], "fri": [["11:00", "18:00"]], "sat": [["11:00", "18:00"]], "sun": [["11:00", "18:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Mon 11:00–18:00; Thu 11:00–20:00; Fri 11:00–18:00; Sat 11:00–18:00; Sun 11:00–18:00', 'ChIJYWLHOqJYwokRmkVum_hd7Ss', 4.4, 1856.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 90, '96 St (6)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJYWLHOqJYwokRmkVum_hd7Ss', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The+Jewish+Museum&query_place_id=ChIJYWLHOqJYwokRmkVum_hd7Ss', 'https://thejewishmuseum.org', '+1-212-423-3200', ARRAY['art_museum', 'museum', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('neue-galerie-new-york', 'Neue Galerie New York', 'museum', 'The Neue Galerie New York is a museum of early twentieth-century German and Austrian art and design on the Upper East Side of Manhattan in New York City. It is located in the William Starr Miller House at 86th Street and Fifth Avenue. Established in 2001, it is one of the most recent additions to New York City''s Museum Mile, on Fifth Avenue. In 2026, the museum and the Metropolitan Museum of Art announced that the two institutions would merge in 2028.', 'The Neue Galerie New York (German for "New Gallery") is a museum of early twentieth-century German and Austrian art and design on the Upper East Side of Manhattan in New York City. It is located in the William Starr Miller House at 86th Street and Fifth Avenue. Established in 2001, it is one of the most recent additions to New York City''s Museum Mile, on Fifth Avenue. In 2026, the museum and the Metropolitan Museum of Art announced that the two institutions would merge in 2028.', 'Manhattan', 'Upper East Side-Carnegie Hill', '1048 5th Ave, New York, NY 10028', 40.781264, -73.9603267, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZO_G9823lyPPY03hGKo08d3oNYt8XUj4FN_QeEA3mCPe0PvfsioHBwqjHXZCJfEKjvevJX00caORve6wvKEVnVmhuYfthNnGfJlMAGQNG6VG6-IrgxfkxLjUJMNHBim5jtUyyB7S3yTIOfe_AJjEpHb=s4800-w736', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNQVDwiIkFOi86M0ndkfc904aeVfyir4V6WB_Kh2kGiBlF-4mw9QBrsqSVkCqKvN5kBSOrOaNqKhphTXW6IHbUDR-wsu6U-6olIbbRNS1AA9qBbh5fUWigmSnMnxDApeZeOYS-1-KTmonE3AcFs1bjL=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM8g51jhGV-R5e-y-_Fh1QmplTvLjM_ynqwjpM6QEnr13ndmNqh48upLAOQNsQiu_0VAhxSjhmt1x4uXqDYdINU-iRQtIh1ZQV_rGba0XghQkyMJvGuEdswqUYDrIGmGb9OhiuGELfT6r_M=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOC1hd6oitYZ3mNxF_l-SWfUANyFQZNut7X5nFHgxwolcRk55Q2haPbiUXcmYfjJqoLdRD-EBO5F6YQl8e0S6OUWQXEYKP8smgNLEbQ2Gz07KYcr6F_YaXI0xVPgoxoiI1VmILmm2R_112Za3XBIrLu=s4800-w800']::text[], NULL,