  ('eataly-nyc-flatiron', 'Eataly NYC Flatiron', 'other', NULL, NULL, 'Manhattan', 'Midtown South-Flatiron-Union Square', '200 5th Ave, New York, NY 10010', 40.742045, -73.9900845, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPo6sDtCZM52gNCGakECpN8z6B_CfAltQvslWp_sP02NZpEAA_PI7J7vIF0pGhow6dbVwZlXKKRjg5ME5LjLXYLS7iCxHFZ5cj5SiQpS_1eXyLJ63o5XLh7kSQWdw7MOmJmSgZMZSeq=s4800-w750', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM6i8gswV9gppBl31OecjEJ3jxEpUYsvVEIpajtS_ZL8m5gfrv7WrrIYelyCiddNcybPOTBhzX8Yh3t3Pfr0zmYVPWvUO_CKnLMmVt7GWx0NK8wg9UkSOrOJLQhB8vxPVWuK8l5I4Yywp4v=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPCXbpFiYcyxtda9M_vHtbnWZMnoIvW7KNK77qRU3O8Vgrkj07GV5pqMgbR22xwDc0b077ZA9ciYWojE3WgTxSW4RqWgZ5JP2yDAH0d1i25qwD_JUzAFzRYtA2MCCXX32UAEUk1GegxnPL7armGEQb2=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOdNt5UPKb69sSF7oc9jrDHmHifpKSfn0Qf6vzps3z_4QXEDghKkfREvFgsPYgT3NWZG6VZVFN5uTOYy060HbejL3YyoZPGjcRc6Xk00jTBLHgG6qGJyewpVf_2yZIaau8jAJ5g4hz7Hr_jt6UX9lw=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["07:00", "23:00"]], "tue": [["07:00", "23:00"]], "wed": [["07:00", "23:00"]], "thu": [["07:00", "23:00"]], "fri": [["07:00", "23:00"]], "sat": [["07:00", "23:00"]], "sun": [["07:00", "23:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 07:00–23:00', 'ChIJaeKcEaRZwokRcllXm5cM7J0', 4.4, 10413.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '23 St (R,W)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJaeKcEaRZwokRcllXm5cM7J0', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Eataly+NYC+Flatiron&query_place_id=ChIJaeKcEaRZwokRcllXm5cM7J0', 'https://www.eataly.com/us_en/stores/nyc-flatiron', '(212) 229-2560', ARRAY['indoor']::text[]),
  ('hamilton-grange-national-memorial', 'Hamilton Grange National Memorial', 'landmark', NULL, NULL, 'Manhattan', 'Manhattanville-West Harlem', '414 W 141st St, New York, NY 10031', 40.8213605, -73.9473024, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMUkYzlRGjSbrlaIotflj8-J_poQRbz_ucGMhsgZjHt4K_RA--2V-ISfrcj3-nQERLlB733anQxX4RGdIImYYwc-z1aVhfnEzxRixvdIlUxdhljrGFC4pVOG9ezZwa-sJOnrvoyyJuceasV2g=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOMB-1TlnGSZEwF87bGotweKle6TJbxNgTeIm8Y-lCgD2a2RbsmvNYnHHJSqOcv6pVc-loTAs2l2KpWmAikUnYVlLEzhqPRVLkSBowWbEQF5Iwq9j_FIURB_wSokxKTyrOHVBrfeJnh6FCq=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZP073HJOipTFRP-kF3NrUVqPZLBrkZd2eTC-u_IgzZBo8jXhWMSo9ewvIjOmVURUVMjXwqFQR1oTp4NfnemUrWd_wG7St27A4bXi9ubiXXrcVw85TY1-m59Ql_Yv5kazwmoqGmwiRN308o=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOeRUsBP4XwPXqPqjzjxDGQcaEwjJN40EH4KVYeKUlxVvgkIjWrH-ZmDx2Rf8zn-2ZwUQ0oFI__8KR1vX8fNXbhDCkvKO2KeTD8UnoL0pXFUZif8Aq4agDwHFdXdibrWoMSD9KoWv3kdLyR9g=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": null, "tue": null, "wed": [["10:00", "16:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "16:00"]], "fri": [["10:00", "16:00"]], "sat": [["10:00", "16:00"]], "sun": [["10:00", "16:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Wed 10:00–16:00; Thu 10:00–16:00; Fri 10:00–16:00; Sat 10:00–16:00; Sun 10:00–16:00', 'ChIJ5wFJxXr2wokRQEmdWil_bEw', 4.5, 981.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 90, '135 St (C,B)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJ5wFJxXr2wokRQEmdWil_bEw', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Hamilton+Grange+National+Memorial&query_place_id=ChIJ5wFJxXr2wokRQEmdWil_bEw', 'https://www.nps.gov/hagr/index.htm', '(646) 494-5366', ARRAY['museum', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('morris-jumel-mansion', 'Morris-Jumel Mansion', 'museum', 'The Morris–Jumel Mansion is an 18th-century historic house museum in the Washington Heights neighborhood of Upper Manhattan in New York City, United States. It is the oldest extant house in Manhattan, having been built in 1765 by British military officer Roger Morris, and was also home to the family of socialite Eliza Jumel in the 19th century. The New York City government has owned the house since 1903. The house''s facade and interior are New York City designated landmarks, and the building is a National Historic Landmark and a contributing property to the Jumel Terrace Historic District and the Dominican Historic District.', 'The Morris–Jumel Mansion (also known as the Morris House, Mount Morris, Jumel Mansion, and Morris–Jumel Mansion Museum) is an 18th-century historic house museum in the Washington Heights neighborhood of Upper Manhattan in New York City, United States. It is the oldest extant house in Manhattan, having been built in 1765 by British military officer Roger Morris, and was also home to the family of socialite Eliza Jumel in the 19th century. The New York City government has owned the house since 1903. The house''s facade and interior are New York City designated landmarks, and the building is a National Historic Landmark and a contributing property to the Jumel Terrace Historic District and the Dominican Historic District.
Roger Morris developed the house for himself and his wife Mary Philipse Morris, but only lived there until 1775. Continental Army General George Washington used the mansion as his temporary headquarters for one month in late 1776, during the American Revolutionary War, after which British and Hessian officers occupied the house until 1783. After the British evacuation of New York, the house passed through multiple owners over the next three decades, being used variously as a residence and a tavern. The Jumels bought the house in 1810, living there intermittently until the late 1830s; the Jumel family and the related Chase family then occupied the house consistently until 1887. After being sold twice more, the house was owned by the Earle family from 1894 to 1903. After the city acquired the mansion, it reopened as a museum on May 29, 1907, and was operated by the Washington Historic Association. The house has undergone renovations in the 1930s, 1940s, and 1980s.
The house, designed with elements of the Federal, Georgian, and Palladian styles, has a raised basement and three above-ground stories. It has a wooden facade with a double-height portico facing south and an octagonal annex in the rear. The interior consists of a kitchen in the basement; a parlor, library, and dining room on the first floor; bedrooms on the upper floors; and wide central hallways. The museum''s collection includes furniture, decorations, household items, and personal items belonging to its former occupants. The museum also presents performances and events at the house. Both the museum''s exhibits and the house''s architecture have received positive commentary, and the mansion has been featured in several media works.', 'Manhattan', 'Washington Heights (South)', '65 Jumel Terrace, New York, NY 10032', 40.8344548, -73.9385727, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPwW9ygc6V473wnD1LxulxsH2j-ksopuBJlfLfBb92heUT1Gl3U8T5oM2DRFBwTNH95VpRbzz47LRFLdkj5dYUN5aexlesbhJSqH5V8cM9OL_IO6GXiY2q1tkesCWtvqQZOd1j_MONZWSo=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOM_hLUGlJB55Wzj9dLsauJfBkh641umPvONBiEZMnX7pGX1NtUh7LiFpbefqiYjdjFoj5kgrmN_1oyWFIlW00q6ZSSrvV_7RWgzVcp-pis_KUqFpNqDYsaAxGTYxg5ozPJ5xLotSBCL0Y=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPkUENNARp6XsS5Sihu4L-70opfNO52RmOisFLp-BMapgQAHJ2IvGxd0ZapilvfGu8Ts3ZomtdCeFS0zQGIOEnarwbk08AXIi4mbDegageJ-kPFsHWkPgXbVrKD5IkRYBfMj6zF0fdqb6ME4A=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMC_IQmDqbViDy3oIwQpwJSqWeiqbp1LEOkndpP5RS_qIVNaX3x40odTXShfrvAb6mwWvezy8n6-vSs7vqt7R3KoSCNQcToCt9N8NYKNuAA5rDjSK2g5Vewjs-ZM-SV_rRE_QpEtI1tRWM5=s4800-w800']::text[], NULL, 'Th 13:00-16:00; Fr,Sa 11:00-16:00', 'ChIJqTIQToL2wokRKbmUA423_YY', 4.5, 571.0, ARRAY['wheelchair_limited']::text[], NULL, NULL, 90, '163 St-Amsterdam Av (C)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJqTIQToL2wokRKbmUA423_YY', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Morris-Jumel+Mansion&query_place_id=ChIJqTIQToL2wokRKbmUA423_YY', 'https://www.morrisjumel.org/', '(212) 923-8008', ARRAY['museum', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('fort-tryon-park', 'Fort Tryon Park', 'park', 'Fort Tryon Park is a public park located in the Washington Heights and Inwood neighborhoods of the borough of Manhattan in New York City. The 67-acre (27 ha) park is situated on a ridge in Upper Manhattan, close to the Hudson River to the west. It extends mostly from 192nd Street in the south to Riverside Drive in the north, and from Broadway in the east to the Henry Hudson Parkway in the west. The main entrance to the park is at Margaret Corbin Circle, at the intersection of Fort Washington Avenue and Cabrini Boulevard.', 'Fort Tryon Park is a public park located in the Washington Heights and Inwood neighborhoods of the borough of Manhattan in New York City. The 67-acre (27 ha) park is situated on a ridge in Upper Manhattan, close to the Hudson River to the west. It extends mostly from 192nd Street in the south to Riverside Drive in the north, and from Broadway in the east to the Henry Hudson Parkway in the west. The main entrance to the park is at Margaret Corbin Circle, at the intersection of Fort Washington Avenue and Cabrini Boulevard.
The area was known by the local Lenape tribe as Chquaesgeck and by Dutch settlers as Lange Bergh (Long Hill). During the American Revolutionary War, the Battle of Fort Washington was fought at the site of the park on November 16, 1776. The area remained sparsely populated during the 19th century, but by the turn of the 20th century, it was the location of large country estates.
Beginning in January 1917, philanthropist John D. Rockefeller Jr. bought up the Tryon Hall estate of Chicago industrialist C. K. G. Billings and several others to create Fort Tryon Park.  He engaged the Olmsted Brothers firm to design the park and hired James W. Dawson to create the planting plan. Rockefeller gave the land to the city in 1931, after two prior attempts to do so were unsuccessful, and the park was completed in 1935. Rockefeller also bought sculptor George Gray Barnard''s collection of medieval art and gave it to the Metropolitan Museum of Art, which from 1935 to 1939 built the Cloisters in Fort Tryon Park to house the collection.
The park is built on a high formation of Manhattan schist with igneous intrusions and glacial striations from the last ice age. The park''s design included extensive plantings of various flora in the park''s many gardens, including the Heather Garden, which was restored in the 1980s. Besides the gardens and the Cloisters, the park has extensive walking paths and meadows, with views of the Hudson and Harlem Rivers. Fort Tryon Park was added to the National Register of Historic Places on December 19, 1978, and was designated a New York City scenic landmark in 1983.', 'Manhattan', 'Washington Heights (North)', 'Riverside, Dr To Broadway, New York, NY 10040', 40.8625608, -73.9312995, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNx2BJo-Z2gtskOwzdvqSJilaQ2VLIVX-21YsVM9A9TzTWmrwa96H_IHdxPgbOOvh8eo5HgQWXeqTJLp_veHak7JI6CrGEVLJZJVh2c7jssfz8WbxIeci3srGe-XT0sQUCCWBqYbMn1l9fT=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOqpv8mIcQt3yrKqFfV5YGEPnJsF53UyUQHV3wAf4d4r4nMR0A4l1N42aFLcoYz_GnaXkMaFJJbpWarU9RY5KHXUh5uBwBdbh_jwVFfdqIEafxAh9YqlUlFSBsgTKm0OfCI8Qsy=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOPt86dtec5PDtD2Prt9QhJcyI-5ThyFhjCh_EmxorAjDRzHZPJd8hz8jWBJdOArEFs34bUPG-SyE0WU7EPuCmFTAhEH0u0DNidUhwIJ47bYhGLMxdCcrB7SZr0Bv_RG0wSPRojnBbI4uMljIOn2Ajp=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM2VpNzLsB4hbuj2JDQv1D10-74CD1zxg6jYpzUC4t77ZAwT2zM4vKJPoAnykb7PJCH2RbN1D2rCZB_6-zN7es3LcCn8cWdG9iHtUyVetZsAv-UrG-yl6LKQ4-fbc7jCO0PIPsmlPdVQvJY3A=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "01:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–01:00', 'ChIJTZ18cAH0wokR1HfVR86mzEA', 4.7, 8480.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '190 St (A)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJTZ18cAH0wokR1HfVR86mzEA', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Fort+Tryon+Park&query_place_id=ChIJTZ18cAH0wokR1HfVR86mzEA', 'https://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/fort-tryon-park', '(212) 795-1388', ARRAY['park', 'outdoor']::text[]),
  ('inwood-hill-park', 'Inwood Hill Park', 'park', 'Inwood Hill Park is a 196 acres (79 ha) public park in the Inwood neighborhood of Manhattan, New York City, operated by the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation. On a high schist ridge that rises 200 feet (61 m) above the Hudson River from Dyckman Street to the northern tip of the island, Inwood Hill Park''s densely folded, glacially scoured topography contains the largest remaining old-growth forest on the island of Manhattan. The area is also known as the Shorakapkok Preserve, shorakapkok meaning ''the sitting place'' in the Munsee language used by the Wecquaesgeek tribe who inhabited the area for nearly 700 years. Unlike other Manhattan parks, Inwood Hill Park is largely composed of natural areas, consisting of mostly wooded, non-landscaped hills.', 'Inwood Hill Park is a 196 acres (79 ha) public park in the Inwood neighborhood of Manhattan, New York City, operated by the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation. On a high schist ridge that rises 200 feet (61 m) above the Hudson River from Dyckman Street to the northern tip of the island, Inwood Hill Park''s densely folded, glacially scoured topography contains the largest remaining old-growth forest on the island of Manhattan. The area is also known as the Shorakapkok Preserve, shorakapkok meaning ''the sitting place'' in the Munsee language used by the Wecquaesgeek tribe who inhabited the area for nearly 700 years. Unlike other Manhattan parks, Inwood Hill Park is largely composed of natural areas, consisting of mostly wooded, non-landscaped hills.', 'Manhattan', 'Inwood Hill Park', 'Payson Ave. &, Seaman Ave, New York, NY 10034', 40.8721829, -73.924776, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOSHtqx2rBAmbayo1AvgkRck7Or2g6uiNKR3jXNgGfyW7PHZkkDOtmM-B2EmSBdLbtye5jPlbx9r_4rommipEcGdVWGaIm3LfqpZHSwHDDtgxU64dkFsTIIzYZFp2bH-Gv1fiibve48lcvc6A=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZO-l8vgVBg1rHFJUuCYt