  ('new-york-historical-society', 'New-York Historical Society', 'museum', 'The New York Historical is an American history museum and library on the Upper West Side of Manhattan in New York City. The society was founded in 1804 as New York''s first museum. It presents exhibitions, public programs, and research that explore the history of New York and the nation. The New York Historical Museum & Library has been at its present location since 1908. The granite building was designed by York & Sawyer in a classic Roman Eclectic style. The building, along Central Park West between 76th and 77th Streets, is a New York City designated landmark. A renovation, completed in November 2011, made the building more accessible to the public, provided space for an interactive children''s museum, and facilitated access to its collections.', NULL, 'Manhattan', 'Upper West Side (Central)', '170 Central Prk W, New York, NY 10024', 40.7793487, -73.9739079, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMv96b34NyF4Yk_mLTWHL7-bP56Thm5VfNJGs7W5jl_q9Vi3j58bH-cyjs77NgNKrt4DhEsPizgdxfGbcXjmLz5VmZqr0_2-FcflU1G7xqkqWNhh0RCsuusXxKSsl_HYiz1SpDxTrKTaY9x=s4800-w730', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMjC1hlS_ZetmnnG7Ph4WD3zzOgCvTPFMAS5yAalCr99fJSyLsO7YXd1f0JfSpGaxKQvvtGBK5TFwGgNzJsLRt_kWJosjnyJIvatg85bwhA4NAdBgMxUeXen2VMRPkpwi7Fbi0lkr7sxqs_=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOvXShOc9lpgQrkMo6UvQXMrfwFJfwcQCb8jPL8XmsFFltWCfKAqHvNbCdG7-IgZ_hMkekFxbAq8cQ7H96zklU1xknmIL7QdRjEtL0B3xt7Kg-ChzLPjQluE3CL9vTi2hfCGF94U7-VT9rS=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMuc2dQfEKKguGieS-NAeMXxlawgZdlL9_xE7lxpJ8Et7nCRZVJvSjgKZnb8sLa6p2JY9hTBtxhI9JeXvnsoqvHbeWQu0L2HmPXaMaWqDt8wCiCiewwolEghSAKdhenyOj7S_N8HBBnrhBu=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": null, "tue": [["11:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["11:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["11:00", "20:00"]], "fri": [["11:00", "20:00"]], "sat": [["11:00", "20:00"]], "sun": [["11:00", "17:00"]]}'::json