  ('tompkins-square-park', 'Tompkins Square Park', 'park', 'Tompkins Square Park is a 10.5-acre (4.2 ha) public park in the Alphabet City portion of East Village, Manhattan, New York City. The square-shaped park, bounded on the north by East 10th Street, on the east by Avenue B, on the south by East 7th Street, and on the west by Avenue A, is abutted by St. Marks Place to the west. The park opened in 1834 and is named for Daniel D. Tompkins, Vice President of the United States.', 'Tompkins Square Park is a 10.5-acre (4.2 ha) public park in the Alphabet City portion of East Village, Manhattan, New York City. The square-shaped park, bounded on the north by East 10th Street, on the east by Avenue B, on the south by East 7th Street, and on the west by Avenue A, is abutted by St. Marks Place to the west. The park opened in 1834 and is named for Daniel D. Tompkins, Vice President of the United States.', 'Manhattan', 'East Village', 'E 10th St, New York, NY 10009', 40.726429499999995, -73.9817841, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPGqXP7TEfr7tlP6ssQVi_xdompehWncLQYFJg2tpBHY5UuVwcC7LKeeTrW9gpjan2EjZ_fB0USBB5yXA9YE6-uOjnC_TV1VxDB8VmzuzA8vxOIYFp57B9WKX7iYw5lzVSMzmiZfto2VheSRQ=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMvOc4mgxA1qChdgBVOjzS1z0ahVN4kt1eSmnUOvW84UZ9sXpFjEYTzO-QHbzIlUIQjl9QKyMN8xInKrUbpqBHYxMac_tdNOfILDWqqKzl3EOekBNTnJXITERC2-yrY5EcikC2OJZL-IILx=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMJaHxP0H8471e0a1-UaXU8bGKAXK8jNky2xrKVjzFhKMPxsWQ8amibnH4T9NaqWfGt9iNFjcFWvxDkzYhev8HYbFG38xwH-B_U9WigPNMP50z_0gZuIQljhYTPum_mUMpK-xmjKaA5mRSS=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMKO-mo1o3D2exqRwBGGyiuGNSy-m1FtqCD5AMEvK-SdmOCoEHV-yNdyGVYPhJYy78WJy7fJD0Vt3fW9BkFDxPa6h8QSzn-QYnVzHfylYZBwz9vTRhcM2u5sw-rsHhF2Vvwyps3mNY_kG6yXQ=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "24:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "24:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "24:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "24:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "24:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "24:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "24:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–24:00', 'ChIJgTDll51ZwokRVjN7KXztwXY', 4.4, 5991.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '1 Av (L)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJgTDll51ZwokRVjN7KXztwXY', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Tompkins+Square+Park&query_place_id=ChIJgTDll51ZwokRVjN7KXztwXY', 'https://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/tompkins-square-park/', '(212) 639-9675', ARRAY['park', 'outdoor']::text[]),
  ('washington-square-arch', 'Washington Square Arch', 'landmark', 'The Washington Square Arch, officially the Washington Arch, is a marble memorial arch in Washington Square Park, in the Greenwich Village neighborhood of Lower Manhattan, New York City. Designed by architect Stanford White in 1891, it commemorates the centennial of George Washington''s 1789 inauguration as President of the United States, and forms the southern terminus of Fifth Avenue.', 'The Washington Square Arch, officially the Washington Arch, is a marble memorial arch in Washington Square Park, in the Greenwich Village neighborhood of Lower Manhattan, New York City. Designed by architect Stanford White in 1891, it commemorates the centennial of George Washington''s 1789 inauguration as President of the United States, and forms the southern terminus of Fifth Avenue.', 'Manhattan', 'Greenwich Village', 'Washington Square N, New York, NY 10012', 40.7312185, -73.9970929, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNdxIxi-MHZNYXQvZOWfJTXybyWYYH1I71koClsceJkgF5s6x_aXoO9b5yYh80VeQHfcWmYwyVd9hNGQBI2oEPiKi6bBL-5AWqyTUx8JQFb2Za7YJ9tPSL-NUZwiR_22yfhPgdf-4S7J-SKsg=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMJayogey5VmecGs8a6ciMXsOtNtgyu-vzzSr8FvvCJkiYUQfOMJftUP3z7biNnjKKV6hnatRv4BbBWn2gAVcnYhQaJrUvujheBEh_W08d6Rej8K7-UR1kDiN5CTtVMuHlL9JdBUAhs8kYK8ctq-3SE=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZN_V7SOLU2WsuKTIkIvHAlYMZHX4EoQWYYeG6Zp1i3qbI_ltnRLEHhfGaaKPvV5knIhN0svsDl9BN__bHuWSXC-ywMREPyv4PpJioJCc6S9njINdAWum4MZpKYKchGdNXMKO_FLtCeluJ69=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNKsJUM_U5xWvFlwHdiUl4rUqww2LiAogI_eJXxoXIwzHqRYC3zfcN8pqo6SSlfrjFTvMf1C-iSXeALiKGZpRLeFUGq0ujmZtp89Wy1ThqiEdtSsUaXfxYIbgvniq4fi6JvjIlJAjil0ehg=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "01:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–01:00', 'ChIJXa-d3ZBZwokRGcUkpZc_uC4', 4.7, 2792.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, 'W 4 St-Wash Sq (A,C,E,B,D,F,M)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJXa-d3ZBZwokRGcUkpZc_uC4', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Washington+Square+Arch&query_place_id=ChIJXa-d3ZBZwokRGcUkpZc_uC4', 'https://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/washington-square-park/monuments/1657', '(212) 639-9675', ARRAY['historical_landmark', 'attraction', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('grace-church', 'Grace Church', 'other', 'Grace Church is a historic parish church in Manhattan, New York City which is part of the Episcopal Diocese of New York. The church is located at 800–804 Broadway, at the corner of East 10th Street, where Broadway bends to the south-southwest, bringing it in alignment with the avenues in Manhattan''s grid. Grace Church School and the church houses—which are now used by the school—are located to the east at 86–98 Fourth Avenue between East 10th and 12th Streets.', 'Grace Church is a historic parish church in Manhattan, New York City which is part of the Episcopal Diocese of New York. The church is located at 800–804 Broadway, at the corner of East 10th Street, where Broadway bends to the south-southwest, bringing it in alignment with the avenues in Manhattan''s grid. Grace Church School and the church houses—which are now used by the school—are located to the east at 86–98 Fourth Avenue between East 10th and 12th Streets.
The church reported 903 members in 2015 and 1,056 members in 2023; no membership statistics were reported in 2024 parochial reports. Plate and pledge income reported for the congregation in 2024 was $1,076,959 with average Sunday attendance (ASA) of 309 persons.
The church, which has been called "one of the city''s greatest treasures", is a French Gothic Revival masterpiece designed by James Renwick Jr., his first major commission. Grace Church is a National Historic Landmark designated for its architectural significance and place within the history of New York City, and the entire complex is a New York City landmark, designated in 1966 (church and rectory) and 1977 (church houses).', 'Manhattan', 'Greenwich Village', '802 Broadway, New York, NY 10003', 40.731975, -73.99090199999999, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM2M1nrkei_GRufUYl3TM-zz4Rrip7lWdpLfjsNpTJZA3gYxNmpJRonu3CRl6Y1hGwQ2uiMdErHr7F7KKAt185StRTXLUb1fed-NxGgYw_KZgNd-rBb6jrxS3DQI9E_RMZQYlAdnol-tE4=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNpS7TQOywleXb-Gau0YdOsyn_7Yg-gl5F4YT_d0kr1orN5OBgy5qfNrIDpF9C7h3QDiu-mb6DEbdB0RZ4wEQP7DgHVEXBsSkrBDyLf8139-olukhBSXmLdFk9C3Y7TU_7vEgrB9GvU_VI=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPY5KdNqI_7uCday7dFnT3U4oAZ-oud86qvo6zV4Selb_g7NUk8ZBcam3tYBr3kD4NlK6Yd0LgEhr5mx1hw0_IoWX9u1rPkPawvjpCXcf6YlGqI3N-rs-_Ctc02GgEvdkLtxukt8Nsa7ubo9g=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOh1jEN-AtZh1vgHjN2tpvdWiYVyaahyeZD6c9gNKK3nKBEPxD0x52TEvuae3JtmIP75ATVC6UNME7euS5OBGLJcVIJLs9lUOQDzO8Ka55XKgi-uHmaSBZn32d5MdQJUYQ3konFDhLTjDXI=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["12:00", "17:00"]], "tue": [["12:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["12:00", "19:00"]], "thu": [["12:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["12:00", "15:00"]], "sat": [["12:00", "17:00"]], "sun": [["08:00", "19:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Mon 12:00–17:00; Tue 12:00–17:00; Wed 12:00–19:00; Thu 12:00–17:00; Fri 12:00–15:00; Sat 12:00–17:00; Sun 08:00–19:00', 'ChIJ8akBcZlZwokRlGROGaTkMnM', 4.7, 436.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, 'Astor Pl (6)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJ8akBcZlZwokRlGROGaTkMnM', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Grace+Church&query_place_id=ChIJ8akBcZlZwokRlGROGaTkMnM', 'https://gracechurchnyc.org/', '(212) 254-2000', ARRAY['place_of_worship', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('stonewall-national-monument', 'Stonewall National Monument', 'landmark', 'Stonewall National Monument is a 7.7-acre (3.1 ha) U.S. national monument in the West Village neighborhood of Greenwich Village in Lower Manhattan, New York City. The designated area includes the Stonewall Inn, the 0.19-acre Christopher Park, and nearby streets including Christopher Street, the site of the Stonewall riots of June 28, 1969, widely regarded as the start of the modern LGBTQ rights movement in the United States.', 'Stonewall National Monument is a 7.7-acre (3.1 ha) U.S. national monument in the West Village neighborhood of Greenwich Village in Lower Manhattan, New York City. The designated area includes the Stonewall Inn, the 0.19-acre (0.077 ha; 8,300 ft2; 770 m2) Christopher Park, and nearby streets including Christopher Street, the site of the Stonewall riots of June 28, 1969, widely regarded as the start of the modern LGBTQ rights movement in the United States.
Stonewall National Monument is the first U.S. national monument dedicated to LGBTQ rights and history. President Barack Obama designated it as a national monument on June 24, 2016.', 'Manhattan', 'West Village', '38-64 Christopher St, New York, NY 10014', 40.7335778, -74.00234069999999, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMwdb2RtGDS04PJX0lWXp1nGWc6y5uJNPSLh5n-XAu37q6I7BoOsZEtB9CW45ZafzeVBSMrVXn-B9c6oUEsSANZg6HOJgcCaXm-1lFzRGDyx6eoYNiljCBADNInFuj3OcvzCCHqIbFr4USE2fKSS_KA=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPwkbfYFqZijmhjWee---_APEC2WCzKjMf7VEYFVqoWLbqi9GW2QdTI9a-PQy4uRcCiMbClUf-l7ZTgKY4S4uLDW5k-fgSYgQPcclr8hj9QAhFn8swjV8ANStsGnQcM1PPkHwZQAiAjOi9r=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNKmJcJ0KJYnMSDkB31O5t8PK3SsACv8MB-6mhUXup84Bag7WKgFGQ4CM12KCZ_0eYTOIVhp7ntRDi52ceKoJ16ZLsropLUyDmW8LOOm-5F8r-k-QkAUvPhwJLbYx73wC3W9-MH4NMokoI=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPtiB_iQdwtKH5ZseguYVIhl5fd1-4OuAPU5dYzx3L02JcMcfd91hQS1DES1jpQB6LjfDHZtTv03Cdw4pVOgScUlfbZnLGe_z9L_vpF85pAl0nt4Gz8TKCGvbHtidL1hIwcJIm2nV4j66aYpmS5X9w=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["07:00", "20:00"]], "tue": [["07:00", "20:00"]], "wed": [["07:00", "20:00"]], "thu": [["07:00", "20:00"]], "fri": [["07:00", "20:00"]], "sat": [["07:00", "20:00"]], "sun": [["07:00", "20:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 07:00–20:00', 'ChIJC-exc5RZwokRWb0fbD6ZBTc', 4.5, 676.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, 'Christopher St-Sheridan Sq (1)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJC-exc5RZwokRWb0fbD6ZBTc', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Stonewall+National+Monument&query_place_id=ChIJC-exc5RZwokRWb0fbD6ZBTc', 'https://www.nps.gov/ston/', '(212) 668-2577', ARRAY['indoor']::text[]),
