  ('the-africa-center', 'The Africa Center', 'landmark', 'The Africa Center, formerly known as the Museum for African Art and before that as the Center for African Art, is a museum located at Fifth Avenue and 110th Street in East Harlem, Manhattan, New York City, near the northern end of Fifth Avenue''s Museum Mile. Founded in 1984, the museum is "dedicated to increasing public understanding and appreciation of African art and culture." The Museum is also well known for its public education programs that help raise awareness of African culture, and also operates a unique store selling authentic handmade African crafts.', 'The Africa Center, formerly known as the Museum for African Art and before that as the Center for African Art, is a museum located at Fifth Avenue and 110th Street in East Harlem, Manhattan, New York City, near the northern end of Fifth Avenue''s Museum Mile.  Founded in 1984, the museum is "dedicated to increasing public understanding and appreciation of African art and culture." The Museum is also well known for its public education programs that help raise awareness of African culture, and also operates a unique store selling authentic handmade African crafts.
The Museum has organized nearly 60 critically acclaimed exhibitions and traveled these to almost 140 venues nationally and internationally, including 15 other countries.  Forty of these exhibitions are accompanied by scholarly catalogues.', 'Manhattan', 'East Harlem (South)', '1280 5th Ave, New York, NY 10029', 40.7964179, -73.9493248, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOvc1qkZRGot08CMkBnTGuTCq-Bmf6HfEby9fO17K-omW21rOiXSETl8DBLW1MWEdb2nS31ubDYIHuZQZPmFTBQa-ETnKzJHBgWnu9yMJI3Ntfd5sAqTQeblneqCCAXAZ4O8jB7yvwIF4Wh=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOUG2xcHRkSeLwK7QBAc6yPw9L9CqBPCw-Um6mmPobbt-yWsRXOypEIYMVRGYHsQc5VaGDJS8roAyPiNvUjylMxoxVZpaaq_DCarJ_ZClPMlbJWo6V_zxEeVYFbgHJzjjKA-8SlPKIP2eM=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMk4Pr2kBKjNYggiUBqBeEzNSvCeJc0ZRpNCwIS7iyFxQ_P762uSO-JUXMaGd_OASlQYVoLQ7rJc7nyG_FZEBq6n5xlTgtdnwIgR0psCqkKgs6WkQnwJ2nl9EeTw-WoYQRj0BeMrcsbd0LiFg=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOv-rHrd67cZrf_7qEwNSgwC2MUqZy_g4tPB1t8ubHc9hVJrkVGUqZPawVwWEybjeEELyX6lbvCPS7fqToeIfecuUQaI8tFQhHT2jonghhlR1kYcT9-4shJfoAVqgIfOGHgC15eTIRfo34=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": null, "tue": [["08:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["08:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["08:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["08:00", "17:00"]], "sat": [["08:00", "17:00"]], "sun": [["08:00", "17:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Tue 08:00–17:00; Wed 08:00–17:00; Thu 08:00–17:00; Fri 08:00–17:00; Sat 08:00–17:00; Sun 08:00–17:00', 'ChIJq6pqPhv2wokRPPkifui_-LY', 4.6, 128.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 90, 'Central Park North (110 St) (2,3)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJq6pqPhv2wokRPPkifui_-LY', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The+Africa+Center&query_place_id=ChIJq6pqPhv2wokRPPkifui_-LY', 'https://www.theafricacenter.org/', '(212) 444-9795', ARRAY['museum', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('one-world-trade-center', 'One World Trade Center', 'landmark', 'One World Trade Center, also known as One WTC and the Freedom Tower, is the main building of the rebuilt World Trade Center complex in Lower Manhattan, New York City. Designed by David Childs of Skidmore, Owings & Merrill, One World Trade Center is the tallest building in the United States, the tallest building in the Western Hemisphere, and the seventh-tallest in the world. The supertall structure has the same name as the North Tower of the original World Trade Center, which was destroyed in the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. The skyscraper stands on the northwest corner of the 16-acre (6.5 ha) World Trade Center site, on the site of the original 6 World Trade Center. It is bounded by West Street to the west, Vesey Street to the north, Fulton Street to the south, and Washington Street to the east.', 'One World Trade Center, also known as One WTC and the Freedom Tower, is the main building of the rebuilt World Trade Center complex in Lower Manhattan, New York City.  Designed by David Childs of Skidmore, Owings & Merrill, One World Trade Center is the tallest building in the United States, the tallest building in the Western Hemisphere, and the seventh-tallest in the world. The supertall structure has the same name as the North Tower of the original World Trade Center, which was destroyed in the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. The skyscraper stands on the northwest corner of the 16-acre (6.5 ha) World Trade Center site, on the site of the original 6 World Trade Center. It is bounded by West Street to the west, Vesey Street to the north, Fulton Street to the south, and Washington Street to the east.
The construction of below-ground utility relocations, footings, and foundations for the new building began on April 27, 2006. One World Trade Center became the tallest structure in New York City on April 30, 2012, when it surpassed the height of the Empire State Building. The tower''s steel structure was topped out on August 30, 2012. On May 10, 2013, after the final component of the skyscraper''s spire was installed, it reached a height of 1,776 feet (541 m). Its height in feet references the signing of the United States Declaration of Independence in 1776. The building opened on November 3, 2014; the One World Observatory opened on May 29, 2015.
On March 26, 2009, the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey (PANYNJ) confirmed that the building would be officially known by its legal name of One World Trade Center, rather than its colloquial name of Freedom Tower. The building has 94 stories, with the top floor numbered 104.
The new World Trade Center complex will eventually include five high-rise office buildings built along Greenwich Street, the National September 11 Memorial & Museum, located just south of One World Trade Center where the original Twin Towers stood, and the World Trade Center Transportation Hub to its east. The construction is part of an effort to memorialize and rebuild following the destruction of the original World Trade Center complex.', 'Manhattan', 'Financial District-Battery Park City', '285 Fulton St, New York, NY 10007, USA', 40.7127431, -74.0133795, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMFnKW4G9KfJ-3GJMmvyjFvGl3m8vBUeO46etso_zIGxt9ZfP650GG8UtbkZwD6xjgRDp7BC7nwDSUUhEr4_18XDt94RIGwHTpRuWpng-8fvgNGwleS9Wej_s49Rq9H6nnZChOvv9vjis0=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMvWcMA7R-VMIYlDmU5WQwGexbRqgpeDEvOXzYjyd293GUfDo_KUue8jsw9W8jv-XsnEEriuPppH81C690_SvTsLMZ5PdH0jvi6N6NaDUlOz_u0W3SRGSycodSTic6A2Nqq2zJcHtphhZoL8A=s4800-w612', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZP5xcnDfch51dtKlrLty2GIrvKkSMNy3RRYayL0V-SSiSU-9uLpTs1CHvA_wQt4Qt01NTelaqDWNclj8spxeCPLQifXXamrxjkh-v1SzbX-A9VDxE7mcUt2i7GlBrKIFz05TxvN2X0W5VqH=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZN3m4ZUYxF7FEF4WH64qjYfgAmxZWGFfrPb3YTJqBmmWQLwgIDkVwMTk9UtjSj4t3JcLvLtb0PBbne42dZ2-hCa6ryPpGDQX-P4kwRPOqyELua3l_KPdpivz_Q6l5HCoZ3nFn2lcCsjEJny=s4800-w800']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'ChIJy7cGfBlawokR5l2e93hsoEA', 4.8, 31106.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, 'WTC Cortlandt (1)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJy7cGfBlawokR5l2e93hsoEA', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=One+World+Trade+Center&query_place_id=ChIJy7cGfBlawokR5l2e93hsoEA', 'https://www.wtc.com/', NULL, ARRAY['historical_landmark', 'attraction', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('madame-tussauds-new-york', 'Madame Tussauds New York', 'museum', 'Madame Tussauds New York is a tourist attraction located on 42nd Street in the Times Square neighborhood of Midtown Manhattan in New York City. Madame Tussauds was founded by the wax sculptor Marie Tussaud, and is now operated by the United Kingdom-based entertainment company Merlin Entertainments. The Madame Tussauds New York location opened on November 15, 2000, after seven years of planning.', 'Madame Tussauds New York (UK , US ; the family themselves pronounce it ) is a tourist attraction located on 42nd Street in the Times Square neighborhood of Midtown Manhattan in New York City. Madame Tussauds was founded by the wax sculptor Marie Tussaud, and is now operated by the United Kingdom-based entertainment company Merlin Entertainments. The Madame Tussauds New York location opened on November 15, 2000, after seven years of planning.', 'Manhattan', 'Midtown-Times Square', '234 W 42nd St, New York, NY 10036, USA', 40.7564752, -73.9883888, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOwhUyG4W_-OdEeewTAql7AVQ490TtSUa6dDiwd2HgqaI9XfbyqU6fzFzbr6tmALFaslOS4r_D4BYlrw3XzF9AN3BdjTgxHfmV-8HXQZGHNYRjy4AbsGPz9WQ3JkPbEY8dkBixTMdJBoEyBdg=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPtRfDHLIH3zBPbjtfkDzt7mwgqusMZpPKEUuXNWs7LN0BohGESX32kP8kA8HPGY-GtaX7T9KmK9vCqR3Hq96fmdB52qNEQTfU29_zc26hzntmgAKUTA19NaSO5sqXGhDsJBpjQl_0kQiA_9A=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZN6skn8rasyNA4DIxv-_h_avHzkrhKr6amzS1R133mhaOIVa9rz8fgOa93pDqK87m7EsNrJgSSf4kgY5XUzGgAd-ZNvuSk7tDEDdgxsIkQkHxHULPAXluV1FDsW0otf1NQ4pysCOHK92V0=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOsk00N_Vpjv0LyZlUXFv8FOqd6peg7P2oziSrFWORIL2G2JTQSujXCSOBsaY2DgtH1GqMCFbyNCBxsqhhuX3H54M5_i8qynrDAZiY6bn6BSWkxKg7RBHsoVm4eRPHDr8dhBwBJanFp76NOhg=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "19:00"]], "tue": [["10:00", "19:00"]], "wed": [["10:00", "19:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "19:00"]],