  ('union-square-park', 'Union Square Park', 'park', 'Union Square is a historic intersection and surrounding neighborhood in Manhattan, New York City, United States, located where Broadway and the former Bowery Road – now Park Avenue north of the Square – came together in the early 19th century. Its name denotes that "here was the union of the two principal thoroughfares of the island". The current Union Square Park is bounded by 14th Street on the south, 17th Street on the north, and Union Square West and Union Square East to the west and east respectively. 17th Street links together Broadway and Park Avenue South on the north end of the park, while Union Square East connects Park Avenue South to Fourth Avenue and the continuation of Broadway on the park''s south side. The park is maintained by the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation.', 'Union Square is a historic intersection and surrounding neighborhood in Manhattan, New York City, United States, located where Broadway and the former Bowery Road – now Park Avenue north of the Square – came together in the early 19th century. Its name denotes that "here was the union of the two principal thoroughfares of the island". The current Union Square Park is bounded by 14th Street on the south, 17th Street on the north, and Union Square West and Union Square East to the west and east respectively. 17th Street links together Broadway and Park Avenue South on the north end of the park, while Union Square East connects Park Avenue South to Fourth Avenue and the continuation of Broadway on the park''s south side. The park is maintained by the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation.
Adjacent neighborhoods are the Flatiron District to the north, Chelsea to the west, Greenwich Village to the southwest, East Village to the southeast, and Gramercy Park to the east. Many buildings of The New School are near the square, as are several dormitories of New York University. The eastern side of the square is dominated by the four Zeckendorf Towers, and the south side by the full-square-block mixed-use One Union Square South, which contains a wall sculpture and digital clock titled Metronome. Union Square Park also contains an assortment of art, including statues of George Washington, Marquis de Lafayette, Abraham Lincoln, and Mahatma Gandhi.
Union Square is part of Manhattan Community District 5 and its primary ZIP Code is 10003. It is patrolled by the 13th Precinct of the New York City Police Department. The New York City Subway''s 14th Street–Union Square station, served by the 4, ​5, ​6, <6>​, L​, N, ​Q, ​R, and ​W trains, is located under Union Square.', 'Manhattan', 'Midtown South-Flatiron-Union Square', '201 Park Ave S, New York, NY 10003, USA', 40.735823499999995, -73.9905215, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNIJY3Yhdcab_IXzJkRCgeei6_Y_3xYlbDZWfmHyAMASGeLwCWaF2lrf5Nz4oqG3yq7TlWlGDrBKsSiV08JL0ykPzmDnDWW3xKCUOBkslpKrLoiYGdhTspNHNbBp0T4T9JweK67_Yd6SSCp=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPIMWCqG4jcamE3Z_zNahWiCPTElAPfV7TXoI93EUdyZ1BNB1KIUKIohitIoAv07V0FnR_5h4-dKWRM26-8fDqR_VmUA6-Og2EP-2glr0tU0GRmw0WyDVA7Dbh_mqTmyR7Zf5GwjpeQdLHlkA=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMKum1iINQ7aHCuQMj6_l1zTPCFRboYXL7dXituZknJa8LZKWVBMcic0TDYZnjeTN1yqsWzbjy4E7JkcNd0QlEkvaFMcGeBmU7zV9yCPpE46ABSS6pHnmUM2n9rmKJTpDKTYXyJtYyYW-mz=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNAmM5livhnx7KpFEbv67NaIx0gKpkmndqOhbUaR_tniYUEu6imRPbh6uD1IU7SaUP_46P13RU4Rk-8ReC3-TqNLFFOaymlz907zlrAd_FofoBQq9BbAsaxm5h2Et2AcgU6bicouPTCfUs2=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "01:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–01:00', 'ChIJuwazLZ9ZwokRoDhp6p5_XCo', 4.6, 17405.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '14 St-Union Sq (L,N,Q,R,W,4,5,6)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJuwazLZ9ZwokRoDhp6p5_XCo', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Union+Square+Park&query_place_id=ChIJuwazLZ9ZwokRoDhp6p5_XCo', 'https://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/union-square-park', '(212) 460-1200', ARRAY['park', 'outdoor']::text[]),
