  ('statue-city-cruises-battery-park', 'Statue City Cruises Battery Park', 'landmark', NULL, NULL, 'Manhattan', 'Financial District-Battery Park City', '1 Battery Park Underpass, New York, NY 10004, USA', 40.7019423, -74.0165238, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNiEPgOS9jXYbJQVp-pKGfDS8JpnoHohEN5MRrE_ChKTWJWGOMi4NxAbpSo96wE1gDYKuT0IxzYrPhdU_kY6O3wUWz2vicUTdfYH8QGRqUz77OI_-JKc5yuHF4uub4ShvleNG7LT2AfKOoq8khiuho=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPYXZKdWWqISW-59QFi48AQOYiEpw_mI0Ev-oA6GDInKonny9L96UFpuVEcwhfZjuAz0zZW41nJXdRnRVL9AZ2204TMFxLixgkOzgUpAxm60p0pgt_n-QvRh5V2qt8uYBNuM8GGiT_T9C37=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZONYcL9kl5QJh-t-K280R49n4uZm1dKRHO4xRcfbwfpJaUFlCWXuiLJNGGW_aUZd29J_h4lQxnqVVjxyzl2tSTWy_etFuqiRltqRz3LcJaVe4YFP9b-SoqkJbywN90SPzNZBGbTmTNE_PDI=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOoEiCIZ0PDQQvB-VliXtOHC1_8jXVKdiVtqM71xNqQ2MmisIvY_eYrp1AsDXBDg9c3xtWfVcUge-9ptLtYtLUu3NR66r26nEElLW7Repuwrs5XjZa2h68FQNp_uQv4lpYjo0Q9qBBBIEas=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["08:00", "19:00"]], "tue": [["08:00", "19:00"]], "wed": [["08:00", "19:00"]], "thu": [["08:00", "19:00"]], "fri": [["08:00", "19:00"]], "sat": [["08:00", "19:00"]], "sun": [["08:00", "19:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 08:00–19:00', 'ChIJex6ai6pbwokRbh3cz6wKQ0w', 4.2, 8629.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 45, 'South Ferry (1)/Whitehall St (R,W)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJex6ai6pbwokRbh3cz6wKQ0w', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Statue+City+Cruises+Battery+Park&query_place_id=ChIJex6ai6pbwokRbh3cz6wKQ0w', 'https://statuecitycruises.com/?utm_source=google&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=statue-battery-park-google-listing', '(877) 523-9849', ARRAY['tourist_attraction', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('majestic-theatre', 'Majestic Theatre', 'other', 'The Majestic Theatre is a Broadway theater at 245 West 44th Street in the Theater District of Midtown Manhattan in New York City, New York, U.S. Opened in 1927, the theater was designed by Herbert J. Krapp in a Spanish style and was built for real-estate developer Irwin S. Chanin. It has 1,681 seats across two levels and is operated by The Shubert Organization. Both the facade and interior are New York City landmarks.', 'The Majestic Theatre is a Broadway theater at 245 West 44th Street in the Theater District of Midtown Manhattan in New York City, New York, U.S. Opened in 1927, the theater was designed by Herbert J. Krapp in a Spanish style and was built for real-estate developer Irwin S. Chanin. It has 1,681 seats across two levels and is operated by The Shubert Organization. Both the facade and interior are New York City landmarks.
The facade is designed in a Spanish style with golden brick, terracotta, and stone and is divided into two sections. The western portion of the facade contains the theater''s entrance, with fire-escape galleries and a terracotta pediment above. The eastern portion is the stage house and is topped by archways. The auditorium contains Adam style detailing, steep stadium seating at the orchestra level, a large balcony, and an expansive plaster dome. Due to the slope of the seats, the rear of the orchestra is one story above ground. An interior leads to a large staircase, which connects to the rears of both the orchestra and the balcony. The balcony has extensive decoration, and there are also box seats near the front of the auditorium at balcony level.
The Majestic, Bernard B. Jacobs, and John Golden theaters, along with the Lincoln Hotel, were all developed by Chanin and designed by Krapp as part of a theater/hotel complex. The Shuberts have operated the Majestic since 1930. The Majestic was always intended as a venue for major musical theater productions because of its large size. Among the shows that premiered at the Majestic are Carousel, South Pacific, The Music Man, Camelot, A Little Night Music, and The Wiz. From 1988 to 2023, the theater housed The Phantom of the Opera, which was the longest-running production in Broadway history when it closed.', 'Manhattan', 'Midtown-Times Square', '245 W 44th St, New York, NY 10036, USA', 40.7583598, -73.98807910000001, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPWyJLI1Lp5Q1KGOOMiXS83T9psBZTjCEiGJUvg1dX-czmjax7DTvaQch5fbRJmioSIXTrK9oGj4Xe1B9YvsBbk2wtU5DsXmI5w8TObIGklwKLqpnGlin7r8Gh0Ds385OHSok7ywybYZgPeeQ=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNN7XiDqiMiUEyceaRjxtTFasZ-jUQKfX1EVM0IZ_21pzKZyixsCBN3YoygmsMiRubwgv1D6LebRmfHuLgkTZc41RvETJfyzDhIwjjtecf52A2PvZMa5MSHJEtBImlVAzz8cAJuSiBORg=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPoyuYUPwBmzuhhwRENOMP9OLq7srckiIYiesBB8ZAVJzaDLar3S09rmmsz5QUfkBlkM-5cA52kU13kMTrhSXapIvoLb04yUKk-Jqpdy2CUyH9YgoSPKdYUwf3M1l-c9wUKukQbDTmcz6Ag=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOP_XNbdY50NBfsoD1x9gvQBdC0opvSdQ-qusWxx3DGP-4pOV3XPpFZ8qpBGL1gWo1X-QYTUSr3b7jGBn5RU7QVMpizqBCI4piLEDF9pdoGSWuIm-qo8hvYH5LfnQFv6UV9gFcz1ZDbG29o=s4800-w800']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'ChIJhWqFh1RYwokR-DHQDzkMAag', 4.7, 8514.0, ARRAY['wheelchair']::text[], NULL, NULL, 120, 'Times Sq-42 St (N,Q,R,W,S,1,2,3,7)/42 St (A,C,E)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJhWqFh1RYwokR-DHQDzkMAag', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Majestic+Theatre&query_place_id=ChIJhWqFh1RYwokR-DHQDzkMAag', 'https://shubert.nyc/theatres/majestic/', '(212) 239-6200', ARRAY['performing_arts_theater', 'theatre', 'indoor', 'wheelchair']::text[]),
  ('columbus-circle', 'Columbus Circle', 'landmark', 'Columbus Circle is a traffic circle and heavily trafficked intersection in the New York City borough of Manhattan, located at the intersection of Eighth Avenue, Broadway, Central Park South, and Central Park West, at the southwest corner of Central Park. The circle is the point from which official highway distances from New York City are measured, as well as the center of the 25 miles (40 km) restricted-travel area for C-2 visa holders.', 'Columbus Circle is a traffic circle and heavily trafficked intersection in the New York City borough of Manhattan, located at the intersection of Eighth Avenue, Broadway, Central Park South (West 59th Street), and Central Park West, at the southwest corner of Central Park. The circle is the point from which official highway distances from New York City are measured, as well as the center of the 25 miles (40 km) restricted-travel area for C-2 visa holders.
The circle is named after the monument of Christopher Columbus in the center, which is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. The name is also used for the neighborhood that surrounds the circle for a few blocks in each direction. Hell''s Kitchen, also known as Clinton, is located to the southwest, and the Theater District is to the southeast and the Lincoln Square section of the Upper West Side is to the northwest.', 'Manhattan', 'Upper West Side-Lincoln Square', '848 Columbus Cir, New York, NY 10019, USA', 40.7680797, -73.9818957, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNin0G5ETmjEraGG--f3eoM8FxQsgJyfzcZmClgNDLxNxeBEvMFgLMZgD5soVg-Itx8XR8uPT4nZL_eFmMQ-XzB7BZDzrqwb5h1kr9WdX9TqXHBEQryg9XisqsIzEUdPhClYIEqX4DwnZ4=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZO8TFZtBIz2SeSqYPABUqcjOVOilZ0eyANiKNFxjHOMECpYi-JfGajf_QaSVfcsLN_kla4kZpnN5Bnsk_etTdEIJRe7xa3RtF3zWDUBcMZUcS0XgJHrcTJ4lfArB-bVnwBfQknvNbA7r6M=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPaGl400CF1clyc2WCXwwqztDPpqsvDbqWDUTONP0B07iUkRWw3_LoLJ9logvT9nZ_7f17aiFzGUtw7agG1GzqCuTsb8ZNVfPBEWh3gXDyAVg3R6TkBtOGXRa-_SzQcrUU7Y1ttUTnZAGQb=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNK3Ma8wnuqj21Z7_Be50Deni3hHFBamqDRL38Sbt6se8oMLztZpHXrD7nIwWi96SbqU13pHjxNSXd02XHUsYyf5KffhKl9L6ucyXEQ3U7HxxZjRiVtoweIAuccGobh_oCI7LWZjL3TA44yPA=s4800-w800']::text[], NULL, NULL, 'ChIJDzorOvZYwokRW5XN4_UBY8w', 4.5, 8381.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, '59 St-Columbus Circle (A,B,C,D,1)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJDzorOvZYwokRW5XN4_UBY8w', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Columbus+Circle&query_place_id=ChIJDzorOvZYwokRW5XN4_UBY8w', 'http://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/central-park/highlights/7738', '(212) 639-9675', ARRAY['historical_landmark', 'attraction', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('minskoff-theatre', 'Minskoff Theatre', 'other', 'The Minskoff Theatre is a Broadway theater on the third floor of the One Astor Plaza office building in the Theater District of Midtown Manhattan in New York City, New York, U.S. Opened in 1973, it is operated by the Nederlander Organization and is named after Sam Minskoff and Sons, the building''s developers. There are approximately 1,710 seats in the auditorium, spread across an orchestra level and a balcony. Over the years it has hosted musicals, dance companies, and concerts.', 'The Minskoff Theatre is a Broadway theater on the third floor of the One Astor Plaza office building in the Theater District of Midtown Manhattan in New York City, New York, U.S. Opened in 1973, it is operated by the Nederlander Organization and is named after Sam Minskoff and Sons, the building''s developers. There are approximately 1,710 seats in the auditorium, spread across an orchestra level and a balcony. Over the years it has hosted musicals, dance companies, and concerts.
The Minskoff was designed by Kahn and Jacobs, who designed One Astor Plaza. It was one of the first theaters constructed under the Special Theater District amendment of 1967. The theater''s main entrances are from a passageway connecting 44th and 45th Streets, in the middle of a city block between Broadway to the east and Eighth Avenue to the west. There are escalators leading from the ground floor to the lobby, where further escalators lead to the auditorium. One Astor Plaza''s eastern section is directly above the theater and has to be supported entirely by the theater''s roof.
One Astor Plaza was initially proposed in 1967 without any theaters. The Minskoff Theatre was added during the planning process; in exchange, One Astor Plaza''s developers were allowed to erect a taller building with additional floor area. The first major production at the Minskoff, Irene, was followed by a series of short-lived productions in the 1970s. The theater subsequently hosted long runs such as West Side Story, The Pirates of Penzance, Black and Blue, and Sunset Boulevard in the 1980s and 1990s. Though many of the Minskoff''s early productions were unprofitable, since 2006 it has housed the musical The Lion King, which became the highest-grossing Broadway musical ever in 2014.', 'Manhattan', 'Midtown-Times Square', '200 W 45th St, New York, NY 10036, USA', 40.7579076, -73.9860774, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPg8TwgPfz8OuUGuReBuAWQivWj1-aCjVxSISnNUrc1RfTbX__5NukKgoIFnoD8zIUIadNyj8TncqTxdIh07aB0zMKL0lVXlupCGcd_BOTRxLmlJ8YUg_nYWMqIsuUiB-4O72Qf8nZwHFh3=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPr6eF-64gN6CoJiTF8C5WUBiegkKx8jPbtUCpR12fZJikWTAzpak87ZtBETZ95EUuTDS7AP7nV3KZmZOqrx3OPQ1oYKFiGIf-cU20MsPCfCbdYaLnCBmxbhucuODjU6JYfNs4R9fUbMsRTNQ=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZO3bHN_fJmhYoeMr7fdRjxgI1YTHELBOl0mc_evO-OIYgi-10S5HjxdCF-vBn2OE4tmpnrC8WBEaJOHnQHFP1Hjqn3a3IGOCQ5SaamzoB7qX9-SC7uHJiFUlUI-dPYRLfj5pMG1qgbK9ElE=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMUAFYdfiz_X1a-j-K3kgJm40Pi2b26u5VbT6MLKk8r_n-5Oq5EzThEVPPUvmk54E7W-IAsmxCKuVjAOQM9bFWIhfOzsOa4HSTYECKreQELRdPG42yRS9w3T7OsvVl2qDnuzFfNUWHGXHC0=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["10:00", "20:00"]], "tue": [["10:00", "20:00"]], "wed": [["10:00", "20:00"]], "thu": [["10:00", "20:00"]], "fri": [["10:00", "20:00"]], "sat": [["10:00", "20:00"]], "sun": [["12:00", "18:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Mon 10:00–20:00; Tue 10:00–20:00; Wed 10:00–20:00; Thu 10:00–20:00; Fri 10:00–20:00; Sat 10:00–20:00; Sun 12:00–18:00', 'ChIJB4