  ('j-hood-wright-park', 'J. Hood Wright Park', 'park', 'J. Hood Wright Park is a park of the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation which is located between Fort Washington and Haven Avenue, and between West 173rd and 176th Streets in the Washington Heights neighborhood of Manhattan, New York City. The 6.7 acres (2.7 ha) park includes a playground – which features a model of the nearby George Washington Bridge, which is visible from the park, basketball courts, ballfields, and a recreation center, as well as a dog walk, a cave in the natural rock formations which form the park''s western boundary, and an installation of a piece of modern sculpture, "3000 AD Diffussion Piece" by Terry Fugate-Wilcox.', 'J. Hood Wright Park is a park of the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation which is located between Fort Washington and Haven Avenue, and between West 173rd and 176th Streets in the Washington Heights neighborhood of Manhattan, New York City. The 6.7 acres (2.7 ha) park includes a playground – which features a model of the nearby George Washington Bridge, which is visible from the park, basketball courts, ballfields, and a recreation center, as well as a dog walk, a cave in the natural rock formations which form the park''s western boundary, and an installation of a piece of modern sculpture, "3000 AD Diffussion Piece" by Terry Fugate-Wilcox.
The park is named for the man who formerly owned the site, J. Hood Wright (1836-1894), a banker, financier and philanthropist born in Philadelphia, who lived in a mansion on 175th Street and Haven Avenue.  Wright anonymously gave money to convert the local subscription library into a free library which became a branch of the New York Public Library.
The city acquired the land by eminent domain in 1925, specifically to build a park, which the neighborhood was lacking in. It has been upgraded and renovated, and the cupola of the hexagonal recreation center was restored in 2013. The park is supported by the Friends of J. Hood Wright Park, a neighborhood organization.', 'Manhattan', 'Washington Heights (South)', 'W. 173 St &, Haven Ave, New York, NY 10033, USA', 40.8463679, -73.941493, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNX6QD3847PpvRr79SeUJ-9fYp_SVrGPZDHr6v6zhwHVkuVATfumHoqLhX_WilkCV-6bqrJ4uMos77tdLBbv4xN-ZPvUoaAIVZRNGfVUIFm0W7WreaEYGQKiAVnnPX-nhBWp0rqXx_jjfYm=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZNkI9lHip7iPUkDQxDECIha9QcycTYM_hYNLBG_jEshvE4sJuwep2w-ZOab3gNQwNis0SvJ5XMErOjTaMQEDYrnpPTdUkTe7WPTOdg1HUoNcKpxkj3d2ryn0d8luL0NepoEcJPr3oBe4W0wa6VXTgz2=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZO5h9U8npfRy0XM-DHNNuPPhn6uzNDZbZ-jmMhWlM5LpzZJHboNo23DpPqM86cWoAWkJyhdqRp7IeklzkO0VaaXoRF5_5fq2Bfikl77Hv1WAg-cSdhaUUM9Ls0zBKPYUETdoNPosZro8IlS0Q=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZOjr_bKblMpft8a98Sao2vuluxL6WSqLjKsw0vtLu3hWr4rK5b5nUp6B88X_0csh3SHe5DozWbqb539Xqb6M57yzvuMrm_1gz02293VpiXZnkI96ZzrvavhVN0YCOGSRnbTsL5D5CnOyzM=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "01:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "01:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–01:00', 'ChIJW8Q_N5_2wokREfZXoLWHIEA', 4.6, 1580.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '175 St (A)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJW8Q_N5_2wokREfZXoLWHIEA', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=J.+Hood+Wright+Park&query_place_id=ChIJW8Q_N5_2wokREfZXoLWHIEA', 'https://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/j-hood-wright-park/', '(212) 639-9675', ARRAY['park', 'outdoor']::text[]),
  ('times-square-church', 'Times Square Church', 'other', 'Times Square Church is a Pentecostal congregation located at the Mark Hellinger Theatre on 237 West 51st Street in the Theater District of Manhattan in New York City. Times Square Church was founded by Pastor David Wilkerson in 1987, and bought the Mark Hellinger Theatre in 1991.', 'Times Square Church is a Pentecostal congregation located at the Mark Hellinger Theatre on 237 West 51st Street in the Theater District of Manhattan in New York City. Times Square Church was founded by Pastor David Wilkerson in 1987, and bought the Mark Hellinger Theatre in 1991.', 'Manhattan', 'Midtown-Times Square', '237 W 51st St, New York, NY 10019, USA', 40.7624398, -73.9841342, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPKP0GKTEYs9DjhMOHGPVURSj_WK5MMpdGp_aphEM5dHkV0_BVXO9ArsYHA4Vo0bTqJ1VptMcP2e-IXNdytzjaPffD_AXuF4zRR0WvlZQiBQV-H91G_aWEfHfOVgwtbkNhjyID0tl-DAPJGX28Z4dAD=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZM1dqKjJoHPm_piA_lXO_n5rd4AvK15GmOlbjz_ByLvunAoLWN92vV26clPzfgWxXlD6BQTQ-9XtHAnQXfrRfX_Y4ac_IiMPVMwqc4gnUoNSjFmVsmLNf8gRNdtjU1DFbsUOgxNm-ZO9Qsro5170pge=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPxAzs6bqx8bRqAYbZWLJ-vF_DaqXXI5GepvqMaNbZF0qQ_tTEyYeBVG-wrSvuzuLLh0TEyEHILnJ60rjlS8QvOw7BIsVdE9dYUMWWuFfV46awA3Sshwolhqtpwmrg7CvU-kW5QnkqyvaCDzQ=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPX7lniyDDv406U_ZsUdujtlqvNdKicif2QbXsyu1XewqY0YVncZWTFiy3BTjl9cmumVcZD-3vtszIvZ80DyPgNAx6DlGVR6w-nRJGNcWBRfsyzAsh_k8vSml471Wy9IVaoTFEJ203UkTM8=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": null, "tue": [["09:00", "17:00"]], "wed": [["09:00", "17:00"]], "thu": [["09:00", "17:00"]], "fri": [["09:00", "17:00"]], "sat": null, "sun": [["09:00", "15:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Tue 09:00–17:00; Wed 09:00–17:00; Thu 09:00–17:00; Fri 09:00–17:00; Sun 09:00–15:00', 'ChIJVUGHS1ZYwokRx39CH6zNL5M', 4.7, 1482.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, '50 St (1)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJVUGHS1ZYwokRx39CH6zNL5M', 'https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Times+Square+Church&query_place_id=ChIJVUGHS1ZYwokRx39CH6zNL5M', 'http://www.tscnyc.org/', '(212) 541-6300', ARRAY['church', 'place_of_worship', 'indoor']::text[]),
  ('chelsea-park', 'Chelsea Park', 'park', 'Chelsea Park is a park in the Chelsea neighborhood of Manhattan, New York City, that dates back to 1910. 
The park has sports fields, basketball and handball courts, a children''s playground and space for sitting. The surface is mostly tarmac or artificial turf, with pits for the plane trees and some plots with annual flower plantings. There is a statue to a World War I soldier, the "Doughboy Statue", erected in 1921. The process of approval, funding and clearing the tenements that occupied the site was protracted. The park has since been upgraded several times by the Works Progress Administration and the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation.', 'Chelsea Park is a park in the Chelsea neighborhood of Manhattan, New York City, that dates back to 1910. 
The park has sports fields, basketball and handball courts, a children''s playground and  space for sitting. The surface is mostly tarmac or artificial turf, with pits for the plane trees and some plots with annual flower plantings. There is a statue to a World War I soldier, the "Doughboy Statue", erected in 1921. The process of approval, funding and clearing the tenements that occupied the site was protracted. The park has since been upgraded several times by the Works Progress Administration and the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation.', 'Manhattan', 'Chelsea-Hudson Yards', 'West 27th Street &, 9th Ave, New York, NY 10001, USA', 40.7500587, -74.001196, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPz175OhBp_a4Xuy39LSitJdRz9DCnXOWBej8RE_0ADbPVeJi8ii1PWQj54AFF24DhYP8YBmIsafoO3j9Ojyt1tFcPgk0N7H5cOaU55W6MvSwmT4V_aFIo96OeaupQn4WJvF_FSjWeCfsU=s4800-w800', ARRAY['https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZMylvkHfnHq84Gssul0WmvqR8xav-j3V1h9PDj2Mk1O3kZSJkSyp5vtSqtXf0u-_cRE7aCJQwqVt_34FDXFf_qsIa_xJWggWfURQ6W_gBqlE0IHM_4vXFwOa4WmtCL_dBt-1_PLbU5nqT3IghgxnFV-=s4800-w640', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZPV6nHy7_8gt71UvhhIFHW8p1A2I9RwplvchRUd4CfnapZAoag4FzI1dLWH5f5WPCXsq2F5vgKcYZ2XP4jWwr_a-2kEeN0N79H0JkRsgwPN1FpiHIJAVRxuEwKXBv6jd_pv91VNgvKSuYDX4fSVFmM=s4800-w800', 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/place-photos/AJRVUZP1lYU9MzdsP8zvFmwMpY2PT8szcLrym5iaz9-KyMt7W1DSUVRdeBVcL-GZVUItB_UQursuqfMZAOfM7vc75o59LCYdQ68GjriGnf19iorD26qMswQf1s1ojW9gpcdWbQeJKSi0VdFr_blA=s4800-w800']::text[], '{"mon": [["06:00", "23:00"]], "tue": [["06:00", "23:00"]], "wed": [["06:00", "23:00"]], "thu": [["06:00", "23:00"]], "fri": [["06:00", "23:00"]], "sat": [["06:00", "23:00"]], "sun": [["06:00", "23:00"]]}'::jsonb, 'Daily 06:00–23:00', 'ChIJQ1pGK7dZwokRfVM1hZ1QmU4', 4.4, 1441.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, '23 St (C,E)', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed/v1/place?key=AIzaSyC1g4kcF24ADMnnTKrUSuvmbM1iGQ1qdGA&q=place_id:ChIJQ1pGK7dZwokRfVM1hZ1QmU4', 'https://